item_data.library_note: Normal water that can be collected anywhere. It can be drunk and used as an ingredient.
item_data.name: Clean Water

item_data.library_note: Milk from goats. It's said to be denser than cow's milk and has a unique flavor.
item_data.name: Goats Milk

item_data.library_note: Water sucked up from the ground by grown bamboo. It has a slightly sweet smell.
item_data.name: Water Bamboo

item_data.library_note: A grassy-smelling extract obtained from plants. Not impossible to drink but has a horrible taste.
item_data.name: Plant Essence

item_data.library_note: Water containing a lot of mineral matter. It may be harmful to health if drunk.
item_data.name: Roteswasser Tonic

item_data.library_note: Rain water accumulated at the center of a giant flower. It has the scent of the flower and can be used as a perfume.
item_data.name: Rapwar Water

item_data.library_note: Bubbly water. Many like to drink it cold.
item_data.name: Foamy Water

item_data.library_note: Beautiful-looking water made for appreciation. Not made for consumption.
item_data.name: Jade Water

item_data.library_note: Precious water containing ancient components. It does not get warm easily, so it's always very cold.
item_data.name: Ancient Blue Water

item_data.library_note: A liquid that emits various colors when exposed to light. It becomes normal water if it stays in contact with air for long periods.
item_data.name: Curious Aqua

item_data.library_note: Dirty water containing a lot of impurities. It's said to be an excellent alchemy ingredient.
item_data.name: Black Water

item_data.library_note: A type of weed that is so common that its even hard to give it a name. Its characteristic is that it has no characteristics.
item_data.name: Nameless Grass

item_data.library_note: Roteswasser-made wheat containing a lot of iron. It may cause iron overload if eaten in excess.
item_data.name: Wasser Wheat

item_data.library_note: Completely dry leaf. Often used as firing material because of its high ignitability.
item_data.name: Dry Grass

item_data.library_note: A lettuce that was given this name because its harvest is big enough to make a hill. The taste is normal.
item_data.name: Hill Lettuce

item_data.library_note: A herb with components that purify dirty water. Things in Roteswasser are green because of the soil.
item_data.name: Blue Herb

item_data.library_note: A type of seaweed available at the sea. It's mineral-rich and often used for cooking.
item_data.name: Rishikelp

item_data.library_note: A type of grass that bites if you touch its leaves. The bite is not painful, though, because it's a leaf.
item_data.name: Chomping Grass

item_data.library_note: A leaf with sugar stored. Little known, maybe because of its ordinary looks.
item_data.name: Sweet Leaf

item_data.library_note: A branch from an ancient tree with strong vitality. Many of them can be found under those trees.
item_data.name: Ancient Branch

item_data.library_note: Grass that looks like a hanging bell. Unfortunately, it makes no sound when swung.
item_data.name: Campanula

item_data.library_note: A type of moss that grows underwater. It contains luminous components, so it's always shining.
item_data.name: Glowing Diatom

item_data.library_note: A leaf that makes you happy when you find it. It has the same components as the three-leafed version.
item_data.name: Lucky Clover

item_data.library_note: White clover, but because of the Roteswasser soil, it became green.
item_data.name: Blue Clover

item_data.library_note: A plant with the power of absorbing light. Slightly better when used on a sunny day.
item_data.name: Light Absorbing Grass

item_data.library_note: A leaf often used as a cooking spice. Because of its strong smell, not everybody is a fan.
item_data.name: Rosen Leaf

item_data.library_note: A seed with sharp thorns that can be picked in forests. It's regarded highly as a throwing weapon.
item_data.name: Uni

item_data.library_note: Ancient Uni found in ruins. It's said to be the ancestor of modern Uni.
item_data.name: Ancient Uni

item_data.library_note: Uni found underwater. It has a property of absorbing poison, and that poison is accumulated in the thorns.
item_data.name: Water Uni

item_data.library_note: A type of Uni that is sensitive to heat and turns to charcoal just by being exposed to strong sunlight.
item_data.name: Charcoal Uni

item_data.library_note: A very rare type of Golden Uni. It's negotiated at a higher price than actual gold.
item_data.name: Gold Uni

item_data.library_note: An Uni with thick thorns that look like devil horns. The two thorns are sharp but break easily.
item_data.name: Demon Uni

item_data.library_note: A giant Uni created by selective breeding. The giant thorns can also be used as a building material.
item_data.name: Emperor Uni

item_data.library_note: A flower that can easily be found on roadsides, but it contains components that can be used as ingredients for medicines.
item_data.name: Health Flower

item_data.library_note: A poisonous blue flower growing in all areas of Roteswasser Kingdom.
item_data.name: Northern Wind Flower

item_data.library_note: A poisonous yellow flower growing in all areas of Roteswasser Kingdom.
item_data.name: Sunny Honey Flower

item_data.library_note: A plant that releases mysterious bubbles that look like soap bubbles. The purpose of these bubbles is unknown.
item_data.name: Bubble Grass

item_data.library_note: A three-colored flower that shines like stained glass if light is cast on it. It's said to be the result of selective breeding.
item_data.name: Stained Flower

item_data.library_note: A flower wrapped up by branches that stretch like a cage. The branches are so strong that picking the flower is next to impossible.
item_data.name: Caged Flower

item_data.library_note: White flower that only lives near clean water. Its used to judge whether the water is safe for drinking.
item_data.name: Spring Princess

item_data.library_note: A flower that looks like its wrapped in flames. It's not on fire, but it takes courage to touch it.
item_data.name: Soul Flower

item_data.library_note: A clear resin-made ornament with a rose inside. It's a popular gift among women.
item_data.name: Rose Crystal

item_data.library_note: A rose with a strong scent that blossoms in high places. By drying and smashing the flower, it produces an elegant perfume.
item_data.name: Delphi Rose

item_data.library_note: A cactus that can survive even in harsh terrain. It contains a lot of liquid.
item_data.name: Polar Cactus

item_data.library_note: A flower that blossoms with the smallest amount of light. It releases pollen every hour, precisely.
item_data.name: Timeteller

item_data.library_note: A plant that exists in the whole world. Its also used as a medicinal ingredient since old times.
item_data.name: Taun

item_data.library_note: A tall taun that does not grow everywhere. It has more medicinal components than normal tones.
item_data.name: Tall Taun

item_data.library_note: Branches and leaves with some of the leaves mutated into flowers. It's said to have a certain effect as a medicinal ingredient.
item_data.name: Sapling Branch

item_data.library_note: Moss that adheres to rocks near the water. It's smashed and infused to be used as a medicine.
item_data.name: Medicinal Moss

item_data.library_note: Soil with a lot of nutrients. It's said to be excellent not only to grow plants but also as an alchemy ingredient.
item_data.name: Fertile Soil

item_data.library_note: A dry flower that releases a strong scent. It seems to have almost no scent before it's dried.
item_data.name: Dry Incense

item_data.library_note: The root of a tree that is used as a medicinal ingredient. As the name suggests, it's very bitter.
item_data.name: Bitter Root

item_data.library_note: Red grass used as a medicinal ingredient and dyes. It's red throughout the year, regardless of the season or growth state.
item_data.name: Crimson Grass

item_data.library_note: An oil that oozes out from a certain soil. It's very sticky and hard to remove if it gets on your hands.
item_data.name: Earth's Secret Oils

item_data.library_note: A leaf with a high nutritional value. A sour juice using this leaf once became popular in the capital.
item_data.name: Sage Grass

item_data.library_note: A leaf used as an ingredient for first-aid medicines. It can be easily found on any high ground.
item_data.name: Life Leaf

item_data.library_note: An expensive, rare, and highly effective medicinal ingredient. It's used for nobles and high-ranking people.
item_data.name: Refueling Extract​

item_data.library_note: Water that gushes out from a flower that grows in an area that humans cannot reach. It becomes a medicine when mixed with chemicals.
item_data.name: Yugdore Water

item_data.library_note: Foul-smelling garbage. Because it's harmful to human bodies, you can say it's poisonous in a way.
item_data.name: Stinky Trash

item_data.library_note: Spores released from giant mushrooms. They're not good for human bodies, so they're dangerous to inhale.
item_data.name: Mushroom Powder

item_data.library_note: A seed filled with liquid. Each seed has a liquid with a different type of color and scent.
item_data.name: Mispel Seed

item_data.library_note: It makes a mysterious sound if you try to pull it from the ground. It's hard on the ears but causes no other harm.
item_data.name: Resentful Scream

item_data.library_note: A flower named to celebrate lies and falsehood. Because it's a common flower, the meaning of the name is unknown.
item_data.name: Blessing of Delusion

item_data.library_note: A plant containing a deadly poison that kills giant dragons. When in bloom, it releases a sweet scent to attract prey.
item_data.name: Dragon Flower

item_data.library_note: Crystallized blood. A hard-to-handle material that becomes an excellent medicine and also a poison, depending on the intake amount.
item_data.name: Demon Blood

item_data.library_note: An all-purpose plant that can be fully used as medicinal ingredients. Just infuse it and drink it to feel the effect.
item_data.name: Forest Sage

item_data.library_note: Water trapped inside ice that occasionally falls along with the rain. It's known as tears of celestial beings.
item_data.name: Celestial Tears

item_data.library_note: An extravagant flower that looks like a vibrant sun. Its habitat and cultivation method are all unknown.
item_data.name: Solflower

item_data.library_note: A flower with a powerful medicinal effect. Even someone on the verge of death can quickly recover enough to get back on their feet.
item_data.name: Dunkelheit

item_data.library_note: A clay-like soft sand with a reddish color. Often used to make ceramics and soil.
item_data.name: Soft Sand

item_data.library_note: Sand that can be obtained by breaking rocks. It flares up if in contact with fire.
item_data.name: Burning Sand

item_data.library_note: Finely smashed coral fragments. Because they're so fine, they may look like sand if not observed carefully.
item_data.name: Corail Saber

item_data.library_note: Leaf mold that comes from poisonous plants. Obviously, nothing grows from this.
item_data.name: Polluted Humus

item_data.library_note: Soil mixed with extremely fine glassy stones. Often found along with other ore.
item_data.name: Emerald Glass

item_data.library_note: Soil from the bottom of the water that contains nutrients from various organisms. The presence of this soil is proof that the area is clean.
item_data.name: Seafloor Soil

item_data.library_note: A mud lump. Because it contains many components, it's an ideal alchemy ingredient, but the texture and smell are horrible.
item_data.name: Black Muck

item_data.library_note: Sand that flies around magnetic rocks. It's possible to strengthen the magnetism by processing it.
item_data.name: Vortex Sand

item_data.library_note: A collection of glittering sand. Look closely and you can see the grains are star-shaped.
item_data.name: Glittering Sand

item_data.library_note: Abandoned and weathered brittle stone. It should go back to normal through alchemy processing.
item_data.name: Eroded Stone

item_data.library_note: A rock whose sweetness spreads through your mouth if you lick it. The mystery of the sweetness remains unsolved.
item_data.name: Nectar Rock

item_data.library_note: A type of ore that was given this name because it becomes cloudy when soaked in acid.
item_data.name: Nepheline

item_data.library_note: A stone covered in moss found near beaches and rivers. It's a common sight anywhere you go.
item_data.name: Waterside Moss Stone

item_data.library_note: An incandescent stone that can be extracted from meteorites. It does not contain any special spiritual force.
item_data.name: Ethereal Stone

item_data.library_note: A stone used for pillars of buildings in the ancient past. It's well shaped and easy to be reused.
item_data.name: Ancient Pillar

item_data.library_note: Coral that has become a fossil over a long period. At first glance, it looks like an ordinary stone.
item_data.name: Coral Stone

item_data.library_note: An ore with the power of the wind. When struck and cracked, it releases a wind that is as strong as the impact received.
item_data.name: Breeze Stone

item_data.library_note: A green and yellow stone. It has bolt and air elements and is highly valued in alchemy.
item_data.name: Riverstone

item_data.library_note: A red and blue stone. Despite having the power of fire and ice, it's only used as an ornament outside alchemy.
item_data.name: Blue Flame Riverstone

item_data.library_note: Niter containing heat. While the niter absorbs heat, it emits high-temperature heat.
item_data.name: Hot Saltpeter

item_data.library_note: An ore with magical powers. It's harder than it looks, which makes it a little difficult to process.
item_data.name: Arknite

item_data.library_note: It still glows red due to the heat that is still smoldering inside, and it may spontaneously ignite, occasionally.
item_data.name: Crimson Ore

item_data.library_note: It often has high-purity crystals that take all the heat away, so gloves are essential when touching it.
item_data.name: Aqua Ore

item_data.library_note: An ore with the power of lightning. It's said to be the result of a transformation caused by lightning.
item_data.name: Lightning Ore

item_data.library_note: An ore with stripes that look like an undulating wind. It emits a light-green glow when the wind hits it.
item_data.name: Wind Ore

item_data.library_note: The most famous and common stone in the world. Its properties allow it to mix together with other metals.
item_data.name: Amatite Ore

item_data.library_note: An one that looks like a common stone during the day, but at night, it shines dimly.
item_data.name: Luminous Rock

item_data.library_note: A dark and plain ore. It's commonly used to make armors, but its weakness is being rather heavy.
item_data.name: Pentanite

item_data.library_note: Milky white ore with high hardness. When polished, it's dealt with as an expensive jewel.
item_data.name: Mordenite

item_data.library_note: A golden ore, but it's not gold. When mixed with other metals, it becomes extremely hard.
item_data.name: Goldinite

item_data.library_note: A white and gold ore. It's possible to split the colors by hitting it with a powerful impact.
item_data.name: Degenesis Stone

item_data.library_note: A transparent ore with seven colors of light inside. Its strength sets it apart from other ores.
item_data.name: Septrin

item_data.library_note: An ore encasing a jewel. Because of its extraordinary hardness, taking the jewel out is next to impossible.
item_data.name: Adamant

item_data.library_note: A mysterious crystal that can only be smashed, shaved and melted after alchemy techniques are applied.
item_data.name: Eternal Crystal

item_data.library_note: A fragment of a crystal-like transparent stone. Sometimes jewels are also mixed up in it.
item_data.name: Small Crystals

item_data.library_note: Raw ore that is no longer recognizable after so many substances have been mixed in with the original ore.
item_data.name: Unknown Gemstone

item_data.library_note: Coral that emits light underwater. If processed well as an ornament, it's traded at a very high price.
item_data.name: Glowing Coral

item_data.library_note: A rare, white bead that can be found in giant clams. It's traded at the same value as a jewel.
item_data.name: White Shell Pearl

item_data.library_note: A super rare black bead that can be found in giant clams. It's more rare and valuable than the white ones.
item_data.name: Black Shell Pearl

item_data.library_note: A small fragment of amber. Because of its cheap price, it can be used liberally as an alchemy ingredient.
item_data.name: Amber Fragment

item_data.library_note: Amber with insects and plants mixed inside. It's said to be more valuable than transparent ones.
item_data.name: Amber Crystal

item_data.library_note: Ore with layers of different colors. Because the properties change with the colors, it's difficult to handle.
item_data.name: Three-Colored Stone

item_data.library_note: Crystal that is created from the accumulation of solidified components sucked up by the trees from the ground.
item_data.name: Clear Branch

item_data.library_note: A liquid substance that was sucked up by big trees' roots and crystallized at the branches.
item_data.name: Holy Arbor Crystal

item_data.library_note: Ore that can be obtained in the underworld. A crystal that, like the land, was contaminated by the Philuscha and, therefore, is harmful to the human body.
item_data.name: Underworld Crystal

item_data.library_note: A shiny black ore. It breaks easily, but if processed, it hardens and even becomes jewels.
item_data.name: Black Glitter Stone

item_data.library_note: Raw ore that can show different colors when processed. It's traded at a very high price.
item_data.name: Rainbow Gemstone

item_data.library_note: Finely crushed wood chips. Extremely light and, if scattered on the ground and ignited, can cause a dust explosion.
item_data.name: Dried Lumber

item_data.library_note: A ball of pepper that has hardened like a stone. While convenient to be transported, it's too hard and difficult to shave.
item_data.name: Flint Pepper

item_data.library_note: A plant with seeds inside its body. It explodes with the impact of a bomb and scatters the seeds kept inside.
item_data.name: Explosive Vine

item_data.library_note: Black sand that completely burns out with a lot of smoke just by getting it close to fire.
item_data.name: Flaming Black Sand

item_data.library_note: Lava ore crushed and turned into powder. If blown by the wind, it certainly causes a great disaster.
item_data.name: Magma Powder

item_data.library_note: Basically, it can only be burned, but since paper is a relatively precious item, it's not garbage.
item_data.name: Scrap Paper

item_data.library_note: Bark that was scraped from a tree. It's dry and burns well, so it's often used as a fuel substitute.
item_data.name: Flammable Bark

item_data.library_note: Bark that was scraped from Palma trees. It burns more easily than common bark.
item_data.name: Palma Bark

item_data.library_note: Coconut that often grows in wetlands. While its oil has many applications, it does not taste too good.
item_data.name: Fuel Coconut

item_data.library_note: Oil extracted from plants. It's often used for cooking and is said to be healthier than oil of animal origin.
item_data.name: Natural Oil

item_data.library_note: Amber-colored high-quality oil. A super luxurious item that was extracted over many years from the rocks in a cave.
item_data.name: Amber Oil

item_data.library_note: Ice crystals that release flames. It's hot when close to the hand, but when squeezed, the heat disappears and becomes cold.
item_data.name: Fire and Ice Crystal

item_data.library_note: An extremely rare type of fuel that is called the flame that burns forever.
item_data.name: Eternal Fire

item_data.library_note: Meat obtained from beasts, as the name implies. It's completely blood-free and pre-processed.
item_data.name: Beast Meat

item_data.library_note: Livestock meat raised for food. Meats of not only beasts but also of monsters have appeared in the market.
item_data.name: Fresh Meat

item_data.library_note: A mysterious egg. Since most of the eggs laying around are unfertilized, the eternal mystery continues.
item_data.name: Some Kind of Egg

item_data.library_note: A nut made of an oil-like substance. When smashed and squeezed, it produces a large volume of oil.
item_data.name: Oil Tree Fruit

item_data.library_note: A fruit known as a present from the heavens. Extremely sweet and enjoyed by all ages.
item_data.name: Nectar Fruit

item_data.library_note: Wild potatoes that grow naturally anywhere. The taste may disappoint, but at least it's edible.
item_data.name: Wild Potato

item_data.library_note: Beans found in the forests. While highly nutritious, it may be too eccentric for quite a lot of people.
item_data.name: Portpea

item_data.library_note: A nut with devilish spiciness. It's loved by super spicy food fans, but most people do not even try it.
item_data.name: Red Devil

item_data.library_note: Plant buds that grow from the ground. They are edible, but after they grow and peel, they can no longer be eaten.
item_data.name: Clenoko

item_data.library_note: An apple that is said to be the most delicious in the world. It contains a lot of juice as if it was a drink.
item_data.name: Red King Apple

item_data.library_note: A product made through selective breeding and used as a festival ornament in a certain area. It tastes the same as a normal pumpkin.
item_data.name: Skull Pumpkin

item_data.library_note: A fruit with a fascinating sweetness. However, that sweetness is a poisonous component, so overeating it may be life-threatening.
item_data.name: Venom Nut

item_data.library_note: The interior of the hard shell is filled with sweet juice, and it's enjoyed by adults and children alike as a beverage.
item_data.name: Palma Fruit

item_data.library_note: A type of wild strawberry. They're very acidic, but become sweeter if smashed and heated.
item_data.name: Fresh Berry

item_data.library_note: A highly nutritious nut. Because of its high amount of oil, it's most commonly found processed and turned into oil.
item_data.name: Werder Nut

item_data.library_note: A tomato that is a specialty of Kurken Island. Fresh products are so sweet that they are seen as fruit.
item_data.name: Kurken Fruit

item_data.library_note: The same tree produces fruit with three different tastes, so it's impossible to know the taste until you try it.
item_data.name: Fortune Fruit

item_data.library_note: A grapevine that bears seven-colored grapes. It can be eaten as is, but it's also often used as a dye.
item_data.name: Rainbow Grapevine

item_data.library_note: A sweet and sour fruit. A unique fruit that has not only a square body but square seeds as well.
item_data.name: Summer Gem

item_data.library_note: A fruit that tastes like fresh cream. The disadvantage is that it has a fluffy texture, so it goes bad easily.
item_data.name: Softtail

item_data.library_note: A beehive with sweet honey stored. It's possible to get honey and bee larvae from it.
item_data.name: Beehive

item_data.library_note: A silvery beehive. It produces gray honey with a higher nutritional value than common honey.
item_data.name: Silver Beehive

item_data.library_note: A legendary golden beehive. The beehive itself is made of honey.
item_data.name: Gold Beehive

item_data.library_note: A beehive with a three-level structure. The honey at the core is the most nutritious, but it tastes bitter.
item_data.name: Bee Haven

item_data.library_note: Multiple spherical beehives bundled together. It has holes in all directions for worker bees to go in and out.
item_data.name: Honey Ball

item_data.library_note: A mushroom that spreads its roots on Eiche. Just grill it and it tastes great.
item_data.name: Eicheloa

item_data.library_note: A cluster of mushrooms that grow from a single place. As individual mushrooms, they fall behind in terms of both nutrition and taste.
item_data.name: Mushroom Colony

item_data.library_note: A mushroom with its cap folded. Its cap unfolds quickly when it senses water.
item_data.name: Brodenbits

item_data.library_note: A type of mushroom that is much larger than others. It requires something like an axe to harvest it.
item_data.name: Utopiechampignon

item_data.library_note: A rare mushroom that grows underwater. It has a jelly-like texture and is mostly made of water.
item_data.name: Jellyfish Mushroom

item_data.library_note: A mushroom so giant that people could sit on it. In reality, however, it has no strength, so people cannot sit on it.
item_data.name: Stool of Nature

item_data.library_note: A mushroom named because of its dark blue like the night sky and because the speckled pattern looked like a lady.
item_data.name: Dusk Mushroom

item_data.library_note: A super extreme mushroom with a reproductive power so high that it can fully cover a piece of land shortly after it starts to grow.
item_data.name: Danger Mushroom

item_data.library_note: A mushroom whose cap is made of crystal. The cap is very hard and not edible, but it can be used for decoration.
item_data.name: Jewel Mushroom

item_data.library_note: A mushroom whose tip looks like a crown. Some people call it the 'king mushroom.'
item_data.name: Golden Crown

item_data.library_note: Freshwater fish that lives in areas surrounded by rivers and lakes. A common fish that can be caught pretty much anywhere.
item_data.name: Sardine

item_data.library_note: A large fish that often appears on dining tables. It's consumed in pretty much every region.
item_data.name: Seriole

item_data.library_note: A shellfish that can be found relatively easy at sandy beaches. It only needs to be grilled to taste good.
item_data.name: Pourpremoule

item_data.library_note: A small crab that inhabits sandy beaches and sea shores. A dangerous animal with sharp pincers on its body.
item_data.name: Crab

item_data.library_note: Seashells washed ashore on sandy beaches. They can be used for decoration and as alchemy ingredients.
item_data.name: Pretty Shells

item_data.library_note: A fish that is normally round-shaped, but when surrounded by enemies, it expands its entire body to protect itself with thorns.
item_data.name: Spikey

item_data.library_note: A starfish with multiple thorns on its back. Because of its resemblance with Uni, it gained this name.
item_data.name: Uni Starfish

item_data.library_note: A subspecies of Uni. Because it's a type of sea creature, it can be caught in seawater.
item_data.name: Chestnut​

item_data.library_note: A fish with rainbow-like scales. When swimming as a school, they look like a giant rainbow swimming.
item_data.name: Rainbow Fish

item_data.library_note: A giant fish with a hard skull and a hammer-like shape. It's ferocious and does not taste too good.
item_data.name: Mace Fish

item_data.library_note: A giant fish with wing-like fins. Despite its kind smile, it's rather ferocious.
item_data.name: Stingray

item_data.library_note: A fish that has not changed its appearance since tens of thousands of years ago. It's considered an endangered species.
item_data.name: Myria Fish

item_data.library_note: A fish that is said to live in the deepest depths of the lakes. It's called the lake master, but in reality, there are many of this species.
item_data.name: Lake Master

item_data.library_note: A nautilus with a large and beautiful spiral shell on its back. It's used as a jewel ornament.
item_data.name: Dragonpalace Nautilus

item_data.library_note: A turban shell shaped like a crown. It can be grilled and eaten.
item_data.name: Crown Shellfish

item_data.library_note: A rare fish that inhabits waterfronts deep inside ruins. An endangered species that tastes very good if simmered.
item_data.name: Imperial Fish

item_data.library_note: An insect with a pattern of seven stars on its back. It's said to be active during the night.
item_data.name: Seven Stars

item_data.library_note: An ant that stores sweet nectar in its body to transport it. For adventurers, it's a snack to replenish sugar.
item_data.name: Honey Ant

item_data.library_note: A grasshopper with horns on its head. With these hard horns, it can flick away the opponent in a fight.
item_data.name: Narwhal Grasshopper

item_data.library_note: An insect that flies with its strangely inflated tail shining like a lantern.
item_data.name: Lantern Fly

item_data.library_note: A bee with a rose red part. Its carnivorous and has a poison strong enough to kill small animals.
item_data.name: Rose Bee

item_data.library_note: A giant insect with its entire body wrapped by a strong shell. It stays nonchalant if taunted by kids.
item_data.name: Giant Beetle

item_data.library_note: A dragon-looking insect. While its appearance may mislead many people, it's actually just an insect.
item_data.name: Baby Wyrm

item_data.library_note: A mantis with feathers that look like a red cloak. Contrary to its appearance, it's surprisingly friendly.
item_data.name: Crimson Cloak

item_data.library_note: An insect that only inhabits places where no light can reach, such as the bottom of rivers and depths of ruins.
item_data.name: Spirit Isopod

item_data.library_note: An insect with a body that looks like a jewel. It has absolutely no value as a jewel.
item_data.name: Amber Fly

item_data.library_note: A butterfly with deep blue feathers. The feathers have a composition close to glass and jewels.
item_data.name: Lapis Papillion

item_data.library_note: A golden insect with three prominent horns. Despite its looks, it does not fight well against other insects.
item_data.name: Trihorn

item_data.library_note: An insect that has not changed its appearance since tens of thousands of years ago. It's sometimes dealt with as a type of jewel.
item_data.name: Ancient Bug

item_data.library_note: A hermit crab that settles inside rocks. It opens holes on rocks to build their houses.
item_data.name: Rock Schloss

item_data.library_note: Giant and strong spider's thread. It can be pulled without breaking too easily.
item_data.name: Restraint Silk

item_data.library_note: Grass that produces something like white fluff after blooming. With this white fluff, it's possible to make thread and cloth.
item_data.name: Cotton Grass

item_data.library_note: A vine plant that won't break even when you pull hard on it.
item_data.name: Tough Vine

item_data.library_note: Ivy that lives for hundreds of years as a parasite that clings to large trees.
item_data.name: Arbor Ivy

item_data.library_note: A web produced by a giant queen spider. It's very stiff, but it becomes a soft fiber if wet with water.
item_data.name: Queen Spider Web

item_data.library_note: A thread ball made by a spider by wrapping its arms around it. It's now stiff.
item_data.name: Hug of Arachne

item_data.library_note: A large tree that can be found anywhere. It's very hard and frequently used as a building material.
item_data.name: Eiche

item_data.library_note: A hard and thick log. It's so hard that even cutting it for lumber is a difficult task.
item_data.name: Tough Log

item_data.library_note: A log that stayed floating on the water for so long that it has been completely covered with moss.
item_data.name: Mossy Driftwood

item_data.library_note: A broken branch of a giant tree called the sacred tree. It's so hard that it's nearly impossible to process it.
item_data.name: Holy Arbor Branch

item_data.library_note: A tree that grows in warm areas like southern countries. It's said to produce terribly hard nuts.
item_data.name: Palma

item_data.library_note: A dead tree that has petrified. It looks like a tree, but the texture is close to stone.
item_data.name: Fossil Tree

item_data.library_note: A fallen tree that continues to release miasma after absorbing nutrients from contaminated land.
item_data.name: Miasma Log

item_data.library_note: A tree with lightning powers stored inside. It's said to have been directly struck by lightning.
item_data.name: Lightning Tree

item_data.library_note: A material that can be collected from ancient trees from tens of thousands of years ago. Very hard but can be used as firewood.
item_data.name: Ancient Log

item_data.library_note: A tree of the same variety as the big trees that are thousands of years old. A precious item that cannot be used for cheap things.
item_data.name: Millennial Tree

item_data.library_note: A plant with leaves that resemble bird wings. They are very light and are often carried around by the wind.
item_data.name: Wing Plant

item_data.library_note: A flower that continues to release a smoke signal. But actually, that smoke signal is not smoke but seeds that are dangerous if inhaled.
item_data.name: Smoke Signal Flower

item_data.library_note: A mushroom with a burnt appearance. It may cause a stomachache if eaten by mistake.
item_data.name: Crispy Mushroom

item_data.library_note: Bubble that can be obtained from bubble grass. It does not break easily if touched.
item_data.name: Sky Bubble

item_data.library_note: A purple gas emitted by rotten trees. If inhaled by mistake, it causes discomfort for days.
item_data.name: Rotwood Miasma

item_data.library_note: A branch from a tree that makes its habitat underwater. The air created inside it is released from all over the branch.
item_data.name: Water Holy Branch

item_data.library_note: A hot, fiery gas that is like the breath of a fire dragon. If unleashed indoors, it's sure to start a fire.
item_data.name: Dragon Breath

item_data.library_note: A fragment of a Fairystone. Because it's always shining, a lot of people use it to light their homes.
item_data.name: Fairystone Fragment

item_data.library_note: A black crystal. They're called "Dark Crystals," but don't really have any dark powers.
item_data.name: Dark Crystal Fragment

item_data.library_note: A crystal that shines blue and white. It has a little mystical power, but it's not a sacred power.
item_data.name: Holy Stone Fragment

item_data.library_note: A fragment of animal that drank too much Duet Stock Solution and had its wings petrified.
item_data.name: Rainbow Wing Fragment

item_data.library_note: A fragment of a book containing notes about various magical systems written by a famous magician.
item_data.name: Magic Tome Piece

item_data.library_note: A book containing notes about various magical systems written by a famous magician. The book itself has magical powers.
item_data.name: Old Magic Tome

item_data.library_note: A leaf from the branches of big trees that have crystals attached to them. It's just a leaf, but it has a mysterious power.
item_data.name: Holy Tree Leaf

item_data.library_note: A sphere reminiscent of a celestial body. It's heavy like stone, but it floats in the air when tossed.
item_data.name: Mystic Sphere

item_data.library_note: A fossil of an ancient creature. It contains shapes of creatures that cannot be found even in books.
item_data.name: Ancient Fossil

item_data.library_note: A lump of ice that never melts even under the sun, or if thrown into fire.
item_data.name: Forever Ice Block

item_data.library_note: A rusty piece of rotten iron. Obviously, it's useless in this condition.
item_data.name: Decayed Iron Pieces

item_data.library_note: A rusty and damaged sword. It's more useful to turn it into metallic material than to reforge it.
item_data.name: Rusted Sword

item_data.library_note: A pile of broken everyday tools. It cannot be used as it is, but it can be recycled as material.
item_data.name: Broken Tools

item_data.library_note: A metal that liquefies if heated. It's difficult to handle until you get used to it.
item_data.name: Liquid Metal

item_data.library_note: A sword used in the ancient past. It was made long before even when the Klint Kingdom came into existence.
item_data.name: Ancient Sword

item_data.library_note: A mysterious precious stone found in the body of a Puni. It was taken from the body of a Blue Puni, and the stone is also blue.
item_data.name: Blue Puniball

item_data.library_note: A mysterious precious stone found in the body of a Puni. It was taken from the body of a Green Puni, and the stone is also green.
item_data.name: Green Puniball

item_data.library_note: A mysterious precious stone found in the body of a Puni. It was taken from the body of a Red Puni, and the stone is also red.
item_data.name: Red Puniball

item_data.library_note: A mysterious precious stone found in the body of a Puni. It was taken from the body of a Black Puni, and the stone is also black.
item_data.name: Black Puniball

item_data.library_note: A mysterious precious stone found in the body of a Puni. It was taken from the body of a Silver Puni, and the stone is also silver.
item_data.name: Silver Puniball

item_data.library_note: A mysterious precious stone found in the body of a Puni. It was taken from the body of a Gold Puni, and the stone is also golden.
item_data.name: Gold Puniball

item_data.library_note: Fur extracted from wild animals. It needs to be tanned before being processed.
item_data.name: Animal Hide

item_data.library_note: Fur extracted from animals said to be mythical beasts. It's soft and has a good coat.
item_data.name: Mythical Hide

item_data.library_note: A bone of a giant creature that must be several times larger than humans. It can be used as an ingredient for hard items.
item_data.name: Large Bone

item_data.library_note: A fossil of a creature much larger than humans. It's hard to determine how it looked based on the remaining bones.
item_data.name: Beast Fossil

item_data.library_note: Fossil bones of a water beast that inhabited the water in ancient times. Despite its large size, it's lightweight and strong.
item_data.name: Water Beast Fossil

item_data.library_note: The scale of a water beast that came off while it was swimming fast. These beautiful scales are often found washed ashore.
item_data.name: Water Beast Scale

item_data.library_note: The wings of bats that nest in caves and ruins. They contain components that are toxic to humans.
item_data.name: Cave Bat Wing

item_data.library_note: An abandoned nest of a white swallow. It has a solid structure, with grass and pieces of wood skillfully knitted together.
item_data.name: White Swallow's Nest

item_data.library_note: A dorsal fin of a magical beast. It's edible if processed, but that takes a long time to do and requires a lot of technique.
item_data.name: Beast Fin

item_data.library_note: Hard shell of monsters. It can repel not only the claws and tusks of other monsters but also human weapons.
item_data.name: Beast Shell

item_data.library_note: It can be obtained from magical beasts with scales. It's thinner than shells but has many applications.
item_data.name: Beast Scales

item_data.library_note: Large feather taken from a giant bird. Because they are many times larger than the feathers of normal birds, many items can be made with a single plume.
item_data.name: Giant Bird Feather

item_data.library_note: A big egg of a giant bird. They are valued widely because they are large, nutritious, and tasty.
item_data.name: Giant Bird Egg

item_data.library_note: Horns taken from goats that have reached the end of their life. There seems to be also a practice of using them as part of an amulet.
item_data.name: Goat Horn

item_data.library_note: Sharp claws of special magical beasts. Because it curses those who touch them, they need to be handled with care.
item_data.name: Demon Claws

item_data.library_note: A material obtained from monster goats. It has better thermal insulation properties than normal goat fur and absorbs impact very well.
item_data.name: Fluffy Wool

item_data.library_note: A thin needle used to inject venom. It has a small hole in its tip from which the venom is released.
item_data.name: Poison Needle

item_data.library_note: A wyrm wing. Its thin and strong membrane is used as a material for high-end armor.
item_data.name: Dragon Wing

item_data.library_note: An egg laid by a dragon. It may be found in dragon nests.
item_data.name: Dragon Egg

item_data.library_note: Dragon eyeballs that are said to have mysterious powers. Since there are only two per dragon, it's a precious material.
item_data.name: Dragon Eye

item_data.library_note: The skull of a giant dragon. Giant dragon bones preserving their original shape are hard to find.
item_data.name: Dragon Bone

item_data.library_note: Dragon meat. It's said that whoever eats it becomes immortal, but in reality, this does not happen.
item_data.name: Dragon Meat

item_data.library_note: A hard outer shell peeled off from a stone golem. It's a special stone that protects from any attack.
item_data.name: Guardian Armor

item_data.library_note: A spirit once held by a knight's ghost. They continued to hold onto it even after it became an evil spirit.
item_data.name: Heroic Spirit

item_data.library_note: A huge Puniball. It has a very different size from the regularly eaten ones.
item_data.name: Giant Puniball

item_data.library_note: A horn decoration owned by leader fairies. The horns of adult fairies grow along with this decoration.
item_data.name: Fairy Horn Adornment

item_data.library_note: Sharp monster claws. Getting struck by such huge claws probably means certain death.
item_data.name: Giant Claws

item_data.library_note: A part that corresponds to a golem's heart. It stores the power to move the golem.
item_data.name: Golem Core

item_data.library_note: The power of dragons is stored within. If a wyvern with this scale gets angry, that power is manifested.
item_data.name: Inverted Scale

item_data.library_note: A stone golem's power core. It's unimaginably more powerful than golem cores.
item_data.name: Ether Core

item_data.library_note: An object dropped by monsters. For humans it's garbage, but it may be a treasure for monsters.
item_data.name: Imp's Lost Item

item_data.library_note: Something like a spirit that appeared from the body of a defeated monster. Its identity is still not clear.
item_data.name: Elemental Force

item_data.library_note: The roots of many plants intertwined. Some parts have anabolized, and it's almost a single thread.
item_data.name: Twisted Thorns

item_data.library_note: Curved and sharp monster claws. Being slashed by these things will certainly mean more than just an injury.
item_data.name: Curved Long Nails

item_data.library_note: The crest of running beasts. It has a special shape designed to minimize air resistance when they are running.
item_data.name: Running Beast Crest

item_data.library_note: The tail of a beast that changes its color according to its surroundings. It's said to change color even if cut off from its body.
item_data.name: Phantom Color Tail

item_data.library_note: A sword that was made to hunt cryptids, but as its appearance suggests, it lacked power.
item_data.name: Wolf Beast's Blade

item_data.library_note: A solvent for smooth joining Fairystones and glass. Not very pure when undiluted.
item_data.name: Duet Stock Solution

item_data.library_note: Ore that is required to manufacture hard glass. It can only be obtained in some areas of the Cleria region.
item_data.name: Scintilla Ore

item_data.library_note: A precious Fairystone that can only be found in a mining area of the Cleria region.
item_data.name: Lujada's Fairystone

item_data.library_note: A mysterious ball found inside a Puni's body. It was taken from a Flower Puni and is cherry-red in color.
item_data.name: Pink Puniball

item_data.library_note: A giant Kurken Fruit. It has a thick skin and doesn't taste good, so it's not suitable for eating.
item_data.name: Giant Kurken Fruit

item_data.library_note: Ordinary cow's milk. Sometimes used as an ingredient in cooking.
item_data.name: Cow Milk

item_data.library_note: A mysterious substance said to harbor the power of spirits.
item_data.name: Spirit Catalysts

item_data.library_note: A feather from the Guide Bird. Only those who respond to guidance can possess it.
item_data.name: Guiding Bird Feather

item_data.library_note: A bag containing many uni and flammable powder. When tossed, a huge number of uni are scattered in the air.
item_data.name: Explosive Uni

item_data.library_note: A bomb containing a huge number of thorns. When tossed, the thorns are dispersed in the air.
item_data.name: Craft

item_data.library_note: A simple bomb filled with only powder and highly flammable materials.
item_data.name: Bomb

item_data.library_note: A rectangular-shaped ice bomb. It's filled with a special type of ice that rapidly lowers the surrounding temperature.
item_data.name: Ice Bomb

item_data.library_note: A strongly magnetized sphere. The moment it bursts, it releases the power of lightning to its surroundings.
item_data.name: Plajig

item_data.library_note: A device that, when tossed, explodes and rapidly gathers the surrounding air, causing a gust.
item_data.name: Luft

item_data.library_note: A bomb that assembles three crafts in one. It has a simple structure, but it's as effective as three crafts.
item_data.name: Trio Craft

item_data.library_note: A flower-shaped Bomb. It got this shape to distract the enemies, but it can also be misleading.
item_data.name: Anemo Bomb

item_data.library_note: A melting Ice Bomb. When held for too long, the container becomes all soaked.
item_data.name: Melting Ice Bomb

item_data.library_note: Plajig with stabilized lightning inside its vacuum tube. It's adjusted to extract maximum power.
item_data.name: Lia Plajig

item_data.library_note: A strong version of Luft. It was improved so that it can strengthen the wind power even further.
item_data.name: Edle Luft

item_data.library_note: A magic device that can reverse day and night.
item_data.name: Lunar Lamp

item_data.library_note: A powerful rose bomb. It's kept safely to avoid accidental explosions.
item_data.name: Astro Rose

item_data.library_note: A crystal with ice powers. It feels very cold just by holding it.
item_data.name: Lavinage

item_data.library_note: A powerful bomb. The user must keep a considerable distance to avoid getting hit.
item_data.name: Grazeit

item_data.library_note: An item with strong wind powers. It's said to be strong enough to cause a storm.
item_data.name: Himmel Feather

item_data.library_note: A book that records secret techniques so powerful they are considered taboo.
item_data.name: Forbidden Spell Book

item_data.library_note: A bomb in the shape of a special energy that ensures the powers of fire and ice do not cancel each other out.
item_data.name: Zwei Resonance

item_data.library_note: Two spears with the power of wind and lightning. It's actually a bomb, but the shape of a spear makes it easier to be thrown.
item_data.name: Cross Judgement

item_data.library_note: The origin of Acacia's Grimoire, which can invoke magic just by being opened.
item_data.name: Sourcebook of Acacia

item_data.library_note: A traditional pill made by processing a medicinal herb found on Kurken Island.
item_data.name: Grass Beans

item_data.library_note: A traditional food made with flour. It's made as a preserved food.
item_data.name: Dry Biscuit

item_data.library_note: A miracle potion created by alchemy with the power of bringing back even a person in deep coma.
item_data.name: Nectar

item_data.library_note: A super powerful medicine capable of healing any kind of injury, diseases, and even death.
item_data.name: Elixir

item_data.library_note: An ointment that is said to have been made by a hermit who severed relationships with others. It has a strong grassy smell.
item_data.name: Hermit Ointment

item_data.library_note: An elixir that is said to communicate with the fairyland. It has a good herby smell.
item_data.name: Fairy Elixir

item_data.library_note: A tool that can disperse a solution from medicinal herbs in the form of an mist.
item_data.name: Mist of Silence

item_data.library_note: The greatest medicine that was given a golden heart, the certificate of exceptional efficacy. The apple inside is said to be decorative.
item_data.name: Golden Heart

item_data.library_note: A super strong medicine made from nectar and elixir.
item_data.name: Mythic Nectar

item_data.library_note: A medicine in a gorgeous chalice. It's immensely effective, but discarding the chalice is troublesome.
item_data.name: Eternal Holy Grail

item_data.library_note: Refined oil extracted from fish. It has the power of clearing the mind when licked.
item_data.name: Fish Oil

item_data.library_note: A powder that makes people more war-prone. It's said to extract fighting instincts.
item_data.name: War Powder

item_data.library_note: A harmonica that will convey your feelings and thoughts through its sound, which provides various enhancements.
item_data.name: Energianica

item_data.library_note: It may look like a bouquet, but it's actually made of dangerous elements such as poisonous plants.
item_data.name: Fake Bouquet

item_data.library_note: A tree branch that covers the outside of golden baskets. The branches are tightly intertwined to keep the basket trapped.
item_data.name: Prison of Decline

item_data.library_note: A purely white glass bottle. It's filled with a white mist, which immediately wraps up the surroundings if the glass is broken.
item_data.name: Haze Breath

item_data.library_note: A common horn. Despite being ordinary, it's said that its sound can make any person excited.
item_data.name: Barbaric Horn Whistle

item_data.library_note: A drawing said to have been made by the devil. It gives the enemy the same kind of sorrow depicted in the drawing.
item_data.name: Depiction of a Devil

item_data.library_note: Wings with mystical colors. Spread it over yourself to protect against all kinds of attacks.
item_data.name: Mystic Robe

item_data.library_note: A medicine that gives incredible strength for a moment, but at the same time, it destroys overworked bodies.
item_data.name: Miracle Ebonyal

item_data.library_note: A mysterious hourglass. It's said to provide superior powers while the sand is falling.
item_data.name: Hourglass of Origin

item_data.library_note: A watch that gives power to control time. It changes the flow of time by watching the movement of the stars.
item_data.name: Astronomical Clock

item_data.library_note: It's said that while this is lit, disaster will come to all foes and allies alike.
item_data.name: Cantera of Calamity

item_data.library_note: A music box made based on the music said to have been played by gods.
item_data.name: Prelude of the Gods

item_data.library_note: Handbell inspired by angels and devils. It gives different effects to allies and enemies.
item_data.name: Call of Abyss

item_data.library_note: A gathering tool used to pick grass and flowers. It's more efficient than doing it by hand.
item_data.name: Grass Sickle​

item_data.library_note: A grass sickle used to pick grass and flowers reinforced to be even easier to use.
item_data.name: Silent Sickle

item_data.library_note: A gathering tool essential for making firewood as well as for collecting wood from trees.
item_data.name: Woodcutter's Axe

item_data.library_note: Woodcutter's Axe with finely adjusted wood-chopping sharpness and weight.
item_data.name: Golden Axe

item_data.library_note: The ideal hammer for destroying rocks and crystals. It can be used as a gathering tool.
item_data.name: Hammer

item_data.library_note: An improved hammer with finely adjusted resistance, weight, and power.
item_data.name: Ravage Hammer

item_data.library_note: A fishing rod for private use. It makes any person happy to have their own unique rod.
item_data.name: Fishing Rod

item_data.library_note: A fishing rod made after the rod that is said to have been used by old masters called fishing gods.
item_data.name: Divine Fishing Rod

item_data.library_note: A net that has been improved not only to catch insects but also underwater use.
item_data.name: Catcher's Net

item_data.library_note: An improved capturing net. The finest net that is easy to swing with the minimum amount of resistance.
item_data.name: Master Catcher's Net

item_data.library_note: Shoes that are so light and comfortable to move around in that it's said they harbor the spirit of winds.
item_data.name: Wind Shoes

item_data.library_note: By stretching the rope of light from the jewel in the bracelet, it's possible to visit places that are normally inaccessible.
item_data.name: Emerald Band

item_data.library_note: A candy that creates wind in the mouth while licking.
item_data.name: Air Drop

item_data.library_note: A device that has been improved to summon cryptids. It's made to summon multiple types of beasts.
item_data.name: Summoner's Bell

item_data.library_note: A basic medicine that often used in alchemy. A red liquid with good affinity with fire element materials.
item_data.name: Red Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: A basic medicine that often used in alchemy. A blue liquid with good affinity with ice element materials.
item_data.name: Blue Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: A basic medicine that often used in alchemy. A yellow liquid with good affinity with bolt element materials.
item_data.name: Yellow Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: A basic medicine that often used in alchemy. A green liquid with good affinity with air element materials.
item_data.name: Green Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: A basic medicine that often appears in the synthesis of alchemy. A universal neutralizer with good affinity with all types of materials.
item_data.name: Rainbow Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: A sweet liquid that can be obtained from beehives. It can naturally be used as a cooking ingredient, as well as an alchemy ingredient.
item_data.name: Honey

item_data.library_note: A syrup made from three types of fruit mixed together. It seems to be used quite often as a secret ingredient.
item_data.name: Berry Syrup

item_data.library_note: A powder made by mashing Wasser wheat. It's used as an ingredient in many dishes.
item_data.name: Flour

item_data.library_note: A super spicy powder. It's not available everywhere, but some stores carry it as a medicine.
item_data.name: Devil's Breath

item_data.library_note: A mysterious type of water that moves around by itself. It's said that its movement follows a law.
item_data.name: Puppet Liquid

item_data.library_note: Incredibly pure water free from any kind of impurities. The best among all types of water.
item_data.name: Super Pure Water

item_data.library_note: Portable drinking water trapped in a clear membrane. It can be carried for long periods.
item_data.name: Traveler's Water Orb

item_data.library_note: An ingredient with medicinal components dried and powdered. Very bitter, but good for the body.
item_data.name: Medica Powder

item_data.library_note: Herbs dried and soaked in oil to extract their medicinal components even further.
item_data.name: Doctor's Bottle

item_data.library_note: Sacred water blessed by God. If used as a medicinal ingredient, it may become more effective than with normal water.
item_data.name: Holy Drop

item_data.library_note: A poison sometimes referred to as the devil's water. If used as an ingredient, it can enhance the toxin and make an even more powerful poison.
item_data.name: Taboo Drop

item_data.library_note: Paper made by alchemy. It's stronger than regular paper, and resistant to water and fire.
item_data.name: Zettel

item_data.library_note: The reinforced version of Zettel, the paper made by alchemy. It's water and dust resistant, allowing it to maintain its quality for a long time.
item_data.name: Reinforced Zettel

item_data.library_note: A pearl that was obtained from a big shell, polished carefully, and made into a perfect jewel.
item_data.name: Pearl Crystal

item_data.library_note: An item that was extracted from amber crystal, had its uneven parts removed, and was carefully polished.
item_data.name: Amberlite

item_data.library_note: A transparent light purple jewel. This color appears after the synthesis process.
item_data.name: Spirinite

item_data.library_note: An emerald jewel made by joining emerald glass.
item_data.name: Waking Emerald

item_data.library_note: A jewel made from rainbow gemstone. It was cut at the angle that it looks the most beautiful, then polished.
item_data.name: Arc en Ciel

item_data.library_note: A beautiful bead that fascinates and attracts onlookers. Inside its black glow, it has a rainbow-colored glitter.
item_data.name: Dark Glittering Oval

item_data.library_note: Mainly used as a firelighter. It's environmentally friendly, made with natural materials.
item_data.name: Nitro Chips

item_data.library_note: Gunpowder with elements of bolt. A mysterious powder that releases lightning when lit, instead of fire.
item_data.name: Donour Powder

item_data.library_note: A blueish-white ember that burns endlessly. It's more correct to consider it a gunpowder with the looks of an ember.
item_data.name: Blue Flame Ember

item_data.library_note: Solid fuel made by mixing different types of oil. It does not burn intensely even when ignited.
item_data.name: Mixing Oil

item_data.library_note: A convenient item that ignites just by being hit. Often used in trips and camping.
item_data.name: Flint Charcoal

item_data.library_note: A small bin containing multicolored oil. It's commonly used as a dye.
item_data.name: Colorful Oil

item_data.library_note: A frail burning ice. Because it's very hard to melt, it's frequently used to refrigerate food items.
item_data.name: Solid Ice Fuel

item_data.library_note: Wind and feathers swirling in a transparent water crystal.
item_data.name: Feather Draft

item_data.library_note: A bar made by melting a lump of common ore, gathering only the metallic parts, and shaped.
item_data.name: Ingot

item_data.library_note: An ingot that glows blue. Because of its extreme hardness, it's said to be hard to process.
item_data.name: Startium

item_data.library_note: A black and white ingot with a metallic luster. The two colors are separated completely during the process.
item_data.name: Creaminea
