item_data.name: Fairystone Light EX

item_data.library_note: A pattern found on the Gate of Honor, drawn by Ryza. It's so poorly drawn that not even a polite compliment is suitable.
item_data.name: Scruffy Drawing

item_data.library_note: A hair clip with a Fairystone decoration of fire, the symbol of glasswork.
item_data.name: Flame Hair Clip

item_data.library_note: A brooch with a hammer adornment, the symbol of Fairystone decoration, made by glasswork.
item_data.name: Hammer Brooch

item_data.library_note: A highly concentrated solution that contains more magic than standard Duet Stock Solution.
item_data.name: Duet Stock Solution+

item_data.library_note: A solvent with higher concentration than that of Duet Solvent Solution. It allows for even more detailed processing.
item_data.name: Duet Solvent Solution EX

item_data.library_note: Material found in the ruins of Nemed. It's said to harbor immense powers.
item_data.name: Seeds of Light

item_data.library_note: An improved version of Seeds of Light with the capacity to suppress the explosive power they harbor.
item_data.name: Seeds of Light EX

item_data.library_note: A monitoring device installed by the Chief that stops the function of Clairvoyance.
item_data.name: Disturbing Bell

item_data.library_note: A pseudo-gate generator devised by Emil. It looks like it does not work the way its.
item_data.name: Emil's Tablet

item_data.library_note: A book left by Emil, detailing why Empel has an artificial arm. Its written in symbols.
item_data.name: Emil's Book

item_data.library_note: Metal used in the heart of Faurre's devices. It's a strong material with very good power transmission properties.
item_data.name: True Silver

item_data.library_note: A device that works as a guide to the Code of the Universe. It was dropped by a part of the Code of the Universe.
item_data.name: Chart of Another Sky

item_data.library_note: The necklace that Ryza gave to Fi last summer. It's worn out after just one year.
item_data.name: Fi's Necklace

item_data.library_note: Fi's Necklace repaired. A simple necklace, without any special effect.
item_data.name: Shiny Necklace

item_data.library_note: A pinwheel given by some people to our beloved children, along with a song, wishing for their happiness in the future.
item_data.name: Dancing Bird Pinwheel

item_data.library_note: The Fairystone Compass that has been processed with True Silver. It became more resistant to damage.
item_data.name: Silver Crystal

item_data.library_note: A tool that shows the location of the Code of the Universe gate, created by improving the Chart of Another Sky.
item_data.name: Celestial Globe of Another Sky

item_data.library_note: Very sturdy wood. Suitable for use as a building material.
item_data.name: High Quality Wood

item_data.library_note: Building materials for the construction of a new inn in the village of Rasenboden.
item_data.name: Sturdy Wood

item_data.library_note: A device used in the construction of Kurken Island. It's completely broken and beyond repair.
item_data.name: Broken Ancient Artifact

item_data.library_note: An improved purifier made by Ryza. An engineer, not necessarily an alchemist, can fix it.
item_data.name: New Purifier

item_data.library_note: An item found in the forest by the late husband of an old lady who lives in Sardonica.
item_data.name: Broken Light

item_data.library_note: A lamp made based on a recipe left by the alchemist who founded the city of Sardonica.
item_data.name: Lamp of the Beginning

item_data.library_note: Machine textbook of the people of the Age of God made for the Oren. For beginners, but making the machines is difficult.
item_data.name: Age of God Manual

item_data.library_note: Bones of an old dragon buried in a shrine of dragons in the Underworld. This dragon was unable to return to the world of humans and died.
item_data.name: Dragon Bone Fragment

item_data.library_note: A jewel made by processing bones of old dragons. It harbors the magical powers of powerful old dragons.
item_data.name: Ancient Dragon Gem

item_data.library_note: A box to store things inside. Neither the box or the objects stored ever deteriorate.
item_data.name: Indestructible Box

item_data.library_note: An auxiliary device for Empel. It smooths the movement of an artificial arm.
item_data.name: Auxiliary Prosthesis

item_data.library_note: A large and substantial lump of meat. It offers the original taste of meat.
item_data.name: Wild Meat on the Bone

item_data.library_note: An illustration book left by Federica's father. It was abandoned in the forest for a long time.
item_data.name: Father's Album

item_data.library_note: A purifier that is attached to desalination equipment. It takes the water quality back to the level when there was a fountain in Kurken Island.
item_data.name: Desalination Equipment EX

item_data.library_note: Federica's pendant. It bears a traditional Sardonican crest.
item_data.name: Federica's Pendant

item_data.library_note: A special coral found on a reef island. Has strong water purification powers.
item_data.name: High Quality Coral Stone

item_data.library_note: A high-purity solvent made from rainbow-colored liquid. Used to fuse Fairystones and glass.
item_data.name: "Agnes Luce" Recipe

item_data.library_note: A giant rice ball in the shape of a bomb. The filling is inside is a surprise.
item_data.name: Packed Rice

item_data.library_note: A skewer with grilled chicken and vegetables. Available with sauce or salt.
item_data.name: Roasted Chicken

item_data.library_note: A hamburger made with plenty of meat from wild animals. It has a smell unique to wild meat.
item_data.name: Gibier Burger

item_data.library_note: A sandwich with simple ingredients. It tastes almost the same, no matter who makes it.
item_data.name: Mixed Sandwich

item_data.library_note: Smoked meat with a satisfying taste. A precious food for adventurers because it can be stored for long periods.
item_data.name: Smoked Meat

item_data.library_note: A simple pizza with dried meat and cheese. The ones with extra cheese are popular, it seems.
item_data.name: Dried Meat Pizza

item_data.library_note: Carpaccio made of fresh fish. It's the perfect dish for the summer with its refreshing taste.
item_data.name: Fresh Fish Carpaccio

item_data.library_note: Pot-au-feu with summer vegetables. It's tasty, but you'll sweat a lot if you eat it on a warm day.
item_data.name: Summer Veggie Stew

item_data.library_note: Green pasta made with the image of a forest in mind. Vegetables were kneaded into the dough as well.
item_data.name: Forest Green Pasta

item_data.library_note: Paella with plenty of seafood. Very popular among seafood lovers.
item_data.name: Seafood Paella

item_data.library_note: The color makes it look super spicy, but it's actually mild, with a condensed umami flavor.
item_data.name: Red Chili Soup

item_data.library_note: Steak grilled on a hot crystal plate. It does not leave burn marks or cause oil splatter, but the oil makes it easy for the steak to slide off.
item_data.name: Steak on Crystal

item_data.library_note: A dish that is simply a huge whole roasted fish, but it's one of the most popular, perhaps because of how it looks.
item_data.name: Roasted Monster Fish

item_data.library_note: Omelette rice with demi-glace sauce. A standard menu item that is found in almost any store.
item_data.name: Beef Omelette Rice

item_data.library_note: Vegetables and meat simmered in white sauce. Stew fans will definitely like this one too.
item_data.name: White Sauce Ragu

item_data.library_note: A cute chick doll. It has the perfect size for a hug pillow.
item_data.name: Chick Doll

item_data.library_note: An ornament made by sculpting a crystal. When placed by a window, the shadow of the pattern is projected on the floor.
item_data.name: Crystal Object

item_data.library_note: Dolls of fairies. Because all are handmade, each face is slightly different.
item_data.name: Fairy Doll

item_data.library_note: It looks, feels, and smells like jelly. But it's purely for decoration and cannot be eaten.
item_data.name: Puni Jelly

item_data.library_note: A doll made to look exactly like a real Puni. It's said that not even the person who made it can distinguish it from the real thing.
item_data.name: Puni Doll

item_data.library_note: A stand designed to have an object be placed on it for the purpose of being seen and admired.
item_data.name: Exhibition Stand

item_data.library_note: Lighting equipment with the shape of a lantern. The fire that is the light source is also fake.
item_data.name: Hanging Lantern

item_data.library_note: A small round table for quick meals. It only has room for tea and snacks.
item_data.name: Round Table

item_data.library_note: A luxurious leather-covered sofa. It looks hard, but it's so soft that your body sinks into it.
item_data.name: Leather Sofa

item_data.library_note: The finest sofa designed to provide perfect comfort. If you sit once, you will not feel like standing up.
item_data.name: Chic Sofa

item_data.library_note: A low table with a design that is not too flashy or too simple and yet has presence.
item_data.name: Elegant Low Table

item_data.library_note: A large pendulum clock. Because it rings every hour, it's the perfect piece of furniture for those who care about time.
item_data.name: Pendulum Clock

item_data.library_note: A full 88-key piano. The keys are light so that children and beginners can play it.
item_data.name: Piano

item_data.library_note: A single bed with a simple design. After a few years, it starts to feel cramped.
item_data.name: Cute Bed

item_data.library_note: A luxurious bed made for aristocrats. It's superior sleeping comfort is unforgettable.
item_data.name: Extravagant Bed

item_data.library_note: A barrel, as you know! Whenever you touch or see it, you say 'barrel.'
item_data.name: Barrel

item_data.library_note: A fancy bench. It was designed to match lawns.
item_data.name: Fashionable Bench

item_data.library_note: A table made to be used in gardens. Apparently, it's often used indoors as well.
item_data.name: Garden Table

item_data.library_note: A pot with seasonal flowers. If not watered every day, they dry out very easily.
item_data.name: Potted Plant

item_data.library_note: A plush toy modelled after the Oren. It seems the person who it was modelled after also owns one.
item_data.name: Oren Doll

item_data.library_note: A small bell to notify when the food is ready. It's noisy if rung in excess.
item_data.name: Dinner Bell

item_data.library_note: A decorative object modelled after a legendary sword that only the brave can draw. The blade is not present.
item_data.name: Decorative Sword

item_data.library_note: A bed used in high-end inns in the land of everlasting summer. It provides good sleep even on sweltering nights.
item_data.name: Resort Bed

item_data.library_note: A sofa used in high-end inns. It's meant for people to sit and relax for long periods.
item_data.name: Resort Sofa

item_data.library_note: A cheap table with a slightly high-end table cloth.
item_data.name: Table with Tablecloth

item_data.library_note: A pot with a small palm tree. Because it does not grow large, it does not produce nuts.
item_data.name: Potted Palm

item_data.library_note: A music stand used by maestros and flutists. Just place a music score, and it becomes a piece of interior decoration.
item_data.name: Music Stand

item_data.library_note: It appears to be the manuscript of an ancient book, but the letters on it no longer exist, so it requires translation.
item_data.name: Giant Manuscript

item_data.library_note: A pot with a tree that bears a small fruit. It's said that fairies come to eat those fruits.
item_data.name: Pixie Pot

item_data.library_note: A chair designed after the chairs on which the great elementals sit. Because it's design-focused, it's not comfortable.
item_data.name: Great Elemental's Chair

item_data.library_note: A decorative object in the shape of moving stars. It's said that all astronomers have one.
item_data.name: Celestial Body Model

item_data.library_note: A picture of a rural scenery. Because it's a simple rural landscape, it's not among the most popular.
item_data.name: Farm Photo

item_data.library_note: A picture of scenes of a rural town. Its a famous landscape, but nobody knows where the picture was taken.
item_data.name: Countryside Photo

item_data.library_note: A rocking chair made with lightweight material. It can be easily moved anywhere.
item_data.name: Rocking Chair

item_data.library_note: A very common sofa. It has a wide seat that is long enough to accommodate three people comfortably.
item_data.name: Cute Sofa

item_data.library_note: A very common blackboard. It can be used not only for classes but also personal study and work.
item_data.name: Blackboard

item_data.library_note: Everybody has seen this, but nobody has ever met the weapon craftsman who it was modeled after.
item_data.name: Blacksmith Statue

item_data.library_note: Since it's alive, it naturally needs to be looked after. Should be raised as an important family member, not a piece of furniture.
item_data.name: Goat

item_data.library_note: A fully baked bread. It's soft inside, and even the lightly roasted crust is tasty.
item_data.name: Crisp Bun

item_data.library_note: A stuffed animal in the shape of a pumpkin-headed fairy. A doll modelled after a mischievous fairy.
item_data.name: Pumpkin Doll

item_data.library_note: A sphere with the map of the entire world. Kurken Island is so small that it appears as a dot.
item_data.name: Globe

item_data.library_note: A piece of furniture in the shape of a cannon. It's said that it does not shoot, but it actually shoots.
item_data.name: Transport Cannon

item_data.library_note: An intensely sweet specialty doughnut made in the capital. Empel's favorite.
item_data.name: Ashra Donut

item_data.library_note: Large Kurken Fruits that were grown through proper nutrition and cultivation environment over a long period.
item_data.name: Giant Luceaux Seed

item_data.library_note: Sweets that were put together with an exquisite balance. If touched carelessly, the pile will easily crumble.
item_data.name: Mountain of Sweets

item_data.library_note: A horn that is said to have been made of a dragon horn. In reality, it's made of animal antlers.
item_data.name: Exotic Horn

item_data.library_note: A basket full of apple-scented potpourri. Naturally, it's not edible.
item_data.name: Apple Basket

item_data.library_note: Actual armor worn by knights. It can be worn for self-defense, in case of emergency.
item_data.name: Knight's Armor

item_data.library_note: A big teddy bear. Because of its high price, many girls long for it.
item_data.name: Teddy Bear

item_data.library_note: Please look at the picture rather than the frame. It's a nostalgic photo of an important memory.
item_data.name: Beautiful Picture Frame

item_data.library_note: A convenient broom that moves and cleans any dirt by itself, when it finds it.
item_data.name: Mysterious Broom

item_data.library_note: A gramophone with a special focus on the acoustics. It's a popular piece of furniture, even among those who do not own records.
item_data.name: Phonograph

item_data.library_note: A weasel doll. It appears to be quite popular among people who cannot have pets.
item_data.name: Weasel Doll

item_data.library_note: It's dazzling, and the model looks uncomfortably hot. It surely attracts unnecessary attention.
item_data.name: Shiny Bust

item_data.library_note: Nobody knows who the model was for this glittering bust.
item_data.name: Sparkling Bust

item_data.library_note: A picture of the capital. It seems to have been taken in the morning, when there were few people around.
item_data.name: Photo of the Capital

item_data.library_note: A stuffed toy made with the same weight, texture, and softness as Fi's.
item_data.name: Fi Doll

item_data.library_note: A small house made from various sweets. If overeaten, it can no longer hold the shape of a house.
item_data.name: Candy House

item_data.library_note: A normal cork board that can be found anywhere.
item_data.name: Mini Cork Board

item_data.library_note: An accessory to organize books upright. A slightly convenient piece of furniture.
item_data.name: Books And Bookends

item_data.library_note: A fancy tea set. Because the appearance was prioritized, it's hard to wash the pot.
item_data.name: Tea Set

item_data.library_note: A device that can be useful in synthesis. Not normally used in synthesis involving alchemy.
item_data.name: Synthesis Eqp Set

item_data.library_note: A pile of Uni. They work as preserved food and for self-defense.
item_data.name: Basket of Uni

item_data.library_note: A mushroom-shaped lamp. The cap part issues a soft glow.
item_data.name: Mushroom Shaped Lamp

item_data.library_note: A distorted devil doll. It's warm when hugged.
item_data.name: Small Devil Doll

item_data.library_note: Boomerang with bird feathers. Aerodynamic and easily strikes its targets.
item_data.name: Downwind

item_data.library_note: A crystal ball that can be imbued with magic. It changes color and attribute depending on the magic put into it.
item_data.name: Rainbow Lapis

item_data.library_note: A flask that contains the soul of a three-headed monster. Said to take the soul of an enemy once it has been defeated.
item_data.name: Cerberus Spirit

item_data.library_note: An arrow made of dragon materials. Powerful enough to fly while gouging the ground, but may break the bow.
item_data.name: Draconic Arrow

item_data.library_note: Throwing machete. Is it the machete's weight that tires its wielder, or does it drain their strength?
item_data.name: Maleficus

item_data.library_note: A parchment containing a powerful incantation that can be activated by reading it aloud. Make any mistakes and the spell will not activate.
item_data.name: Calamity Code

item_data.library_note: Cocoa sweet enough to wake you from a deep sleep. There are even some who prefer such sweetness normally.
item_data.name: Sugar Drip

item_data.library_note: Portable fountain overflowing with a medicinal solution. Hard to drink from, but very effective!
item_data.name: Eternal Spring

item_data.library_note: An instrument that emits soothing tones. It is quite heavy and drains the player's strength.
item_data.name: Suonare

item_data.library_note: A cracker that makes a loud bang!
item_data.name: Voltage Liberator

item_data.library_note: A huge weathervane. It is clearly very heavy, and it is said that the wind blows in whatever direction it points.
item_data.name: Windsong Fowl

item_data.library_note: A bell that normally does not ring when shaken, but in an emergency, it emits a calming chime.
item_data.name: Bell of Tranquility

item_data.library_note: A pretty flower that, when planted, sucks up so many nutrients from the soil that it kills the others around it.
item_data.name: Lovely Blossom

item_data.library_note: Is it an object, or some kind of energy mass? It seems rather unstable, and it emits powerful pulses.
item_data.name: Neutronenstern

item_data.library_note: A jar that is extremely lightweight for its size. They say looking at what's inside will make you feel sick.
item_data.name: Violet Cauldron

item_data.library_note: A tree branch that is said to suppress magic. However, there isn't much point in using it by itself.
item_data.name: Seal Branch

item_data.library_note: An old dragon's claw. It looks ancient, but its sharpness has been honed over many years.
item_data.name: Old Dragon's Claw

item_data.library_note: A mysterious stone clothed in the power of water. Since it is the same temperature as the water it always feels cool and soothing.
item_data.name: Water Stone

item_data.library_note: A unique metal that absorbs sound. It is a valuable building material.
item_data.name: Silence Steel

item_data.library_note: A white flower that gleams beautifully in the moonlight. Creatures fascinated by its beauty inhabit the surroundings.
item_data.name: Verdant Moonflower

item_data.library_note: Water in a gourd. The water is said to have special effects.
item_data.name: Heavenly Seawater

item_data.library_note: A fish that appears transparent in water. For this reason, is extremely difficult to catch.
item_data.name: Clearfish

item_data.library_note: A type of fruit shaped like a bird flapping its wings. Popular as a lucky charm.
item_data.name: Pine Fruit

item_data.library_note: A rock that contains a large amount of salt. The purer the rock is, the more intense its pink coloring.
item_data.name: Melocotone

item_data.library_note: A brightly colored clam shaped like a star. Popular not only as a decorative material, but also as food.
item_data.name: Star Clam

item_data.library_note: An insect that feeds on gemstones. They increase the purity of the gemstones they eat, storing them within their bodies.
item_data.name: Gemeater

item_data.library_note: A mushroom with a blade-like cap. In fact, their caps are so sharp that they can be used as knives.
item_data.name: Tsurugi Mushroom

item_data.library_note: A stone so light that it floats on water. Shaped like a flower petal, it is almost indistinguishable from a real petal.
item_data.name: Floating Petal Stone

item_data.library_note: A metal that is said to never rust. Characterized by its bright green hue.
item_data.name: Verdeum Metal

item_data.library_note: A flower with seeds that look like cotton wool. Widely distributed since its seeds are carried by the wind.
item_data.name: Wool Flower

item_data.library_note: A plant whose thick leaves contain a bactericidal solution.
item_data.name: Cleaner Plant

item_data.library_note: Very bitter, but effective for both wounds and colds. It is so bitter that few can consume it in its natural state.
item_data.name: Medicinal Sap

item_data.library_note: Has a hard, scaly bark. Its toughness makes it difficult to harvest.
item_data.name: Immortal Sapling

item_data.library_note: Small rain clouds drifting above the ground. They produce quite heavy rainfall for their size.
item_data.name: Blessed Clouds

item_data.library_note: Wooden ornament. Its use other than as an ornament is unknown, but perhaps it could be a wood substitute?
item_data.name: Carved Relic

item_data.library_note: A plant that resembles a giant sickle. Extremely toxic, so approach with caution.
item_data.name: Reaper's Scythe

item_data.library_note: Threads found after rain and in areas of high humidity. Thin but strong enough to withstand strong winds.
item_data.name: Heavenly Rain Thread

item_data.library_note: An object that has the power to distort the space around it. Contains a powerful energy and quite unstable.
item_data.name: Unstable Lump

item_data.library_note: Nut that can be used as a fire-starter or fuel. Valued by adventurers.
item_data.name: Ignis Nut

item_data.library_note: An old scroll. Nothing is written on it, but the paper itself contains powerful magic.
item_data.name: Ancient Scroll

item_data.library_note: A stone material with molten metal poured into fine crevices. Harder and more ductile than ordinary stone.
item_data.name: Edelhard

item_data.library_note: A versatile base for liquid medicine. Can be combined with other drugs to produce medicines with excellent healing properties.
item_data.name: Medica Solution

item_data.library_note: A poison so deadly that a single drop can kill even the most ferocious of beasts. It vaporizes into an odorless gas when left at room temperature.
item_data.name: Toxited

item_data.library_note: A mysterious sand that turns into jelly when soaked in liquid. Easy to store in dry sand form.
item_data.name: Jelly Sandwich

item_data.library_note: A bright crimson liquid at room temperature. When heated it becomes volatile, type of an explosive.
item_data.name: Crimson Birth

item_data.library_note: Coal that contains more oil than usual. Once ignited, it burns hotter and for a longer amount of time.
item_data.name: Riot Coal

item_data.library_note: A sort of yarn made with extremely hard mineral components. Its high durability compensates for its relative inflexibility.
item_data.name: Vajra Wire

item_data.library_note: Potpourri made from plants that are considered sacred. It is said to have a calming and relaxing effect.
item_data.name: Lumiere Potpourri

item_data.library_note: A device that allows the flow of gases of various compositions in and out. Each type can be stored separately.
item_data.name: Ideal Unit

item_data.library_note: Secret dragon extract that can serve as either poison or medicine depending on how it is used.
item_data.name: Dragon's Tears

item_data.library_note: At first glance, it looks like trendy formal wear, but various weapons are hidden inside it.
item_data.name: Antique Style

item_data.library_note: Hunter's equipment that allows the user to move lightly even in poor environments. Dustproof, waterproof, and heat-resistant.
item_data.name: Hunter's Wear

item_data.library_note: This is a unique improvement upon the royal court's luxurious equipment. Flaunt your power with colorful jewels!
item_data.name: Luminous Gold Armor

item_data.library_note: Used by aristocrats for the glove-throwing tradition when challenging someone to a duel.
item_data.name: Immortal Gloves

item_data.library_note: A special flower that does not wither naturally and is often used as a good luck charm.
item_data.name: Fleur Corsage

item_data.library_note: A metal lamp that contains great magical power. After a long enough period of time, it may even become a home to a spirit.
item_data.name: Lamp of Force

item_data.library_note: Rare jewelry found mainly in the kingdom's western region. Some see the illusion of a shimmering border between the purple and yellow.
item_data.name: Aurora Jewel

item_data.library_note: Extremely powerful painkiller, but even the slightest error in its composition can cause it to become toxic to humans.
item_data.name: Glück Potion

item_data.library_note: A mysterious candelabra that continues to burn without extinguishing and is not hot to the touch.
item_data.name: Torch of the Ages

item_data.library_note: High-grade thread used by royals. Light as a cloud, yet highly durable.
item_data.name: Royal Spun Thread

item_data.library_note: The white sand that blankets Rosca Island. It feels more like ash than regular sand.
item_data.name: White Sand of Eternity

item_data.library_note: A ball of dry grass blown by the wind. It grows by assimilating other plants in its path.
item_data.name: Traveling Grass

item_data.library_note: Metal mined only on Rosca Island. It is thought to be specially formed by its unique environment, but details are unknown.
item_data.name: White Sand Metal

item_data.library_note: An ore with a purple part that contains a lot of magic power and a glassy yellow part.
item_data.name: Ametrite

item_data.library_note: Ore that was left behind by the people who used to live here. It is not in its original form, but it is of great cultural value.
item_data.name: Forgotten Pottery

item_data.library_note: Each of the three tails contains a venom with different properties, any of which will work on any creature.
item_data.name: Desert Cleaner

item_data.library_note: It grows by storing a small amount of water in its body, which is red inside. Valuable as precious moisture in arid regions.
item_data.name: Trifruit

item_data.library_note: The brighter its red flower blooms, the more nutritious it is considered. Sold as a vegetable.
item_data.name: Cactus Blossom

item_data.library_note: It is said to be the souls of the dead. When released into the sky, they always fly in one direction.
item_data.name: Mortal Anima

item_data.library_note: Lower jawbone strengthened by crushing rocks. Countless scars are evidence of its violent history.
item_data.name: Shark Bone

item_data.library_note: Meat of monsters from Rosca Island. A favorite of Dian's.
item_data.name: Exotic Meat

item_data.library_note: A copy of translated literature obtained from travels around Rosca Island.
item_data.name: Kala's Translated Texts (Copy)

item_data.library_note: A rare material obtained from the golden puni on the capital outskirts. Enthusiasts everywhere jump with joy when they manage to get their hands on it.
item_data.name: Golden Puniball

item_data.library_note: Neutralizer dyed crimson that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Crimson Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: Neutralizer as clear as the azure sky that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Azure Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: Neutralizer that is bright green and has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Emerald Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: Neutralizer imbued with a thunderous strength that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Thunder Neutralizer

item_data.library_note: An ingot that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron, making it even stronger than before.
item_data.name: Hard Ingot

item_data.library_note: Cloth that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron, giving it unprecedented flexibility.
item_data.name: Soft Cloth

item_data.library_note: Fiber that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron, making it strong enough to withstand any weight.
item_data.name: Strong Alchemy Fibers

item_data.library_note: Mixed oil that burns longer than ever before, thanks to a formula brewed in an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Flame Mixing Oil

item_data.library_note: Medica Powder with higher potency than before, thanks to a formula brewed in an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Superior Medica Powder

item_data.library_note: Poisonous Liquid with higher potency than before, thanks to a formula brewed in an ancient cauldron.
item_data.name: Strong Poisonous Liquid

item_data.library_note: A crystal that can only be found within a sandstorm.^00It seems to contain a strange sort of power...
item_data.name: Sandstorm Crystal

item_data.library_note: A new key created by Ryza in the land of swirling white sand. It works even upon withered ground.
item_data.name: White Tower Key

item_data.library_note: A key with a reddish-black ore that appears to be the color of blood.
item_data.name: Bloodstone Key

item_data.library_note: A key with white and black feathers on either side.
item_data.name: Fallen Angel Key

item_data.library_note: A key with a charm that seems to pull the beholder into a dream world.
item_data.name: Dream Key

item_data.library_note: A key that is said to be based on the image of the sun being eclipsed by the moon.
item_data.name: Eclipse Key

item_data.library_note: A key with an abundance of achromatic gemstones.
item_data.name: Colorless Crystal Key

item_data.library_note: A key created in the image of an angel, a legendary being.
item_data.name: Divine Wing Ruler Key

item_data.library_note: A key created envisioning the skies of another world.
item_data.name: Master of the Void Key

item_data.library_note: A key that contains the breath of life of the nature itself.
item_data.name: Cradle of Life Key

item_data.library_note: A cloudy white crystal with a power similar to that of the white moon that gives eternal life.
item_data.name: White Moon's Soul

item_data.library_note: An orb that contains the terrifying ability to pull things in and transport them to some other location.
item_data.name: Universe Sphere

item_data.library_note: A wood that is extremely lightweight but very durable. It doesn't even hurt if you drop it on your foot!
item_data.name: Fairywood

item_data.library_note: A heat-resistant container filled with magma. Not hot to the touch, but dangerous when opened.
item_data.name: Mini Volcano

item_data.library_note: A rare flower with seven-colored petals. Rumor has it that if you find one, your wish will come true.
item_data.name: Seven-Color Pansy

item_data.library_note: A tree with flowers that look like little fairies. Said to grow only in certain areas.
item_data.name: Fairy Sapling

item_data.library_note: A stone that combusts above a certain temperature. It must be kept in water so it won't ignite at room temperature.
item_data.name: Lava Rock

item_data.library_note: A mysterious stone that emits a bluish-white light. It is said to fall from the sky when the moon wanes.
item_data.name: Moon Fragment

enemy_data.name: Blue Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Blue Puni is all around the world. Weak but vigorous and grows if left alone.

enemy_data.name: Green Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Green Puni is often found in grasslands and forests. It snaps if its sunbathing is disturbed, but its weak.

enemy_data.name: Red Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Red Puni lives in hot areas. As the temperature drops, it loses its energy.

enemy_data.name: Flower Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Despite its cute appearance, this Puni uses the flowers on its head to lure in prey.

enemy_data.name: Black Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Black Puni. They suddenly leap out of the darkness and feel a sense of fulfilment in surprising adventurers.

enemy_data.name: Silver Puni
enemy_data.library_note: It has a mirror like glossy pout. It is said that luster determines the ranking of the herd.

enemy_data.name: Gold Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Golden glowing Puni. It is said to bring good luck when seen.

enemy_data.name: Lavender Puni
enemy_data.library_note: This Puni has a tentacle that looks like lavender sprout on the top of its head. Its smell is so strong that adventurers don't like it.

enemy_data.name: Big Puni
enemy_data.library_note: They are not merged together, nor fat, they are just originally a plump species.

enemy_data.name: Shining Puni
enemy_data.library_note: This title is only given to those who have survived the grueling competition for survival. The Puni of all the Puni.

enemy_data.name: Rafflesia Puni
enemy_data.library_note: It has a way stronger smell than the Lavender Puni. If you are sensitive to smell, it will cause pain.

enemy_data.name: Darkness Puni
enemy_data.library_note: A huge species of Black Puni. It pops out of darkness like them, but stands out because of its presence.

enemy_data.name: Precious Puni
enemy_data.library_note: Giant Silver Puni. They often go out into the sunlight and boast their brilliance.

enemy_data.name: Giant Weasel
enemy_data.library_note: A common monster that inhabits any forest. It has strong family ties and always hangs out in herds.

enemy_data.name: Bluefin
enemy_data.library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. He is so quick on his feet because of his timid nature.

enemy_data.name: Silky Fur
enemy_data.library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. It produces a fine pelt but is very wary of humans.

enemy_data.name: Scarf Bunny
enemy_data.library_note: A type of the Giant Weasel. It is in search of a fitting scarf and sometimes leave their nests to travel.

enemy_data.name: Night Hunter
enemy_data.library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. Because of the name someone gave it, it is often misunderstood and is actually not a good hunter.

enemy_data.name: Ruined Corrupter
enemy_data.library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel. It is especially violent compared to others within its species and requires vigilance.

enemy_data.name: Hide Stalker
enemy_data.library_note: This one is not just a Giant Weasel. It is capable of defeating monsters larger than itself.

enemy_data.name: Loppy Ear
enemy_data.library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel with large developed ears. Sensitively listens to sounds to avoid threats.

enemy_data.name: Mother Weasel
enemy_data.library_note: Recent research shows that there is a male Giant Weasel Mother, so scholars are thinking of renaming this one.

enemy_data.name: Savage Assassin
enemy_data.library_note: A type of a Giant Weasel that has grown to a huge size for some reason. It likes the way it looks now.

enemy_data.name: Hex Rabbit
enemy_data.library_note: A Giant Weasel transformed by magical power. Can both attack and heal itself with magic.

enemy_data.name: Large Antler
enemy_data.library_note: A monster with a large horn on the top of its head. It is said that the horn is also a sensory organ.

enemy_data.name: Holy Beast of the Stars
enemy_data.library_note: A subspecies of monster characterized by its large horns. It can sense when fellow monsters are in danger by using its horns.

enemy_data.name: Flower Pixie
enemy_data.library_note: A flower fairy awakened by sunlight. Fights to protect her favorite flower garden.

enemy_data.name: Illuminated Sylph
enemy_data.library_note: A flower fairy awakened by the moon. Naturally a night owl, so it always looks sleepy during the day.

enemy_data.name: Flower Gardener
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy who likes to take care of flowers. It fights using the magic powers from the flowers it grows.

enemy_data.name: Zephyr Pixie
enemy_data.library_note: According to one theory, is was formed from an exotic seed carried by the west wind that sprouted to become a fairy.

enemy_data.name: Eternal Guardian
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy that can live forever and watches over flowers and nature. It loves nature and shows no mercy to those who damage it.

enemy_data.name: Blazing Maiden
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy with a sad fate, burning its own flowers with a flame inside itself.

enemy_data.name: Hallowed Spirit
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy who gained sacred power through sunlight. Though it is holy, it is relentless.

enemy_data.name: Plumed Lorelei
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy who loves fruits. When the fruit it grows is taken away, it becomes furious.

enemy_data.name: Elder Fairy
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy who decided to devote its life to an old tree. But that ancient tree predeceased her.

enemy_data.name: Mirage Master
enemy_data.library_note: Mistaking the illusion created by magic for a flower, it continues to protect the flower, without even realizing it's an illusion.

enemy_data.name: Lunaria Angel
enemy_data.library_note: A hedonistic fairy born from the light of the moon. It enjoys life in the corner of a flower garden.

enemy_data.name: Nightmare Spirit
enemy_data.library_note: Born from a flower with the nature to deceive people. It shows people the dreams they don't want to watch.

enemy_data.name: Schwarzwraith
enemy_data.library_note: The reason sightings are so few is that its considered to be imaginary and gives everyone nightmares.

enemy_data.name: Sweet Nocturnal
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy in a black robe. It prefers dark places and is rarely ever seen in public.

enemy_data.name: Moon Veil
enemy_data.library_note: A fairy in a golden costume. They enchant those who see them by dancing gracefully.

enemy_data.name: Stone Golem
enemy_data.library_note: A monster born from the will of a Fairystone. The nature of the Fairystone it's born from determines its character.

enemy_data.name: Rock Puppet
enemy_data.library_note: A monster born from a block of ice charged with magical power. The ice so sharp, even more so than a knife.

enemy_data.name: Jewel Guard
enemy_data.library_note: A Fairystone monster that is devoted to refining its own body. It shines like a gemstone.

enemy_data.name: Fairystone Puppet
enemy_data.library_note: A monster that eats ore and gains its strength. Their territories are veins of ore where Fairystones can be extracted in abundance.

enemy_data.name: Metal Golem
enemy_data.library_note: A monster born from a lava-formed Fairystone. It has a violent temperament like this high temperature inside of it.

enemy_data.name: Meteorite Doll
enemy_data.library_note: A monster born from a meteorite. It contains a special ingredient that is not found anywhere else and its ecology is full of mystery.

enemy_data.name: Earth Master
enemy_data.library_note: It is said that the master was created a long time ago by mixing earth and soil with magic power. It is highly dangerous.

enemy_data.name: Rusty Onyx
enemy_data.library_note: An ore monster with rust colored lines. Its pattern changes depending on the impurities.

enemy_data.name: Colossus Golem
enemy_data.library_note: This ore monster became huge as a result of finding and collecting Fairystones.

enemy_data.name: Eternal Sculpture
enemy_data.library_note: A statue that was made by ancient people with Fairystones, which now has its own will. The creator is unknown.

enemy_data.name: Boulder Soldier
enemy_data.library_note: Artificially created stone soldiers. They have been following orders since they were created.

enemy_data.name: Darkomaton
enemy_data.library_note: Monsters that look like shadows with substance. It is said to appear before children who stay up late at night.

enemy_data.name: Noir Doll
enemy_data.library_note: The end of a soul with too many powerful unfulfilled desires. Wandering around as if driven by something.

enemy_data.name: Cramberry
enemy_data.library_note: A monster characterized by large red fruits. It is said to share its fruit with whoever it likes.

enemy_data.name: Harvest Prayer
enemy_data.library_note: A monster that bears blue-purple fruits. Just as it looks, the fruits taste like blueberries, but it doesn't really share.

enemy_data.name: Horned Sheep
enemy_data.library_note: They are monsters, but can be used as livestock. Everything, including the horns and fur is harvestable and valuable.

enemy_data.name: Ashen Wool
enemy_data.library_note: When they see something moving or red, they rush towards it. A poke with their horns is enough to kill someone.

enemy_data.name: Fluffy Sheep
enemy_data.library_note: A famous monster known for its high-grade wool. Nobles and others in the capital farm it for bedding.

enemy_data.name: Dreamcatcher
enemy_data.library_note: An alert sheep-type of monster. If you can defeat it, your dreams will come.

enemy_data.name: Giant Sheep
enemy_data.library_note: The blood of this monster is thicker than that of a normal sheep. No more, no less.

enemy_data.name: Mindlurker
enemy_data.library_note: It looks scary, but legend has it that it sucks up painful nightmares and takes the pain from you.

enemy_data.name: Mad Beast
enemy_data.library_note: A monster that collects people's memories and turns them into power. Appears in front of those with strong feelings and challenges them to fight.

enemy_data.name: Scaled Armadillo
enemy_data.library_note: A monster covered with a hard outer shell. When threatened, it curls itself up into a ball to protect itself.

enemy_data.name: Intact Carapace
enemy_data.library_note: A monster that protects itself with a reddish outer shell. It is more alert than the normal species and very seamless in defending itself.

enemy_data.name: Tiny Devil
enemy_data.library_note: A round, fluffy little monster. Dangerous because they rush at you whilst running energetically.

enemy_data.name: Ash Demon
enemy_data.library_note: A light-pigmented but energetic little monster. Dangerous because it charges at people as soon as it sees them.

enemy_data.name: Hot Evil
enemy_data.library_note: A cute-looking little monster. Dangerous because it lunges as an expression of affection.

enemy_data.name: Blue Fiend
enemy_data.library_note: A mischievous little monster that is more agile than normal. Dangerous because they rush at you as if they want to play.

enemy_data.name: King Devil
enemy_data.library_note: A small monster that has grown huge with an abundance of magical power. It is also more playful, making it even more dangerous.

enemy_data.name: Storm Elemental
enemy_data.library_note: A crystalline body of magic power. If it is mistaken for a Fairystone and mined, it will go berserk.

enemy_data.name: Icy Crystal
enemy_data.library_note: A crystalline body of magical power tinted pale. If you try to harm it, it will fight back using magic.

enemy_data.name: Spirit of Nature
enemy_data.library_note: A crystalline body of magical power transformed by high concentrations of magic. Eliminates enemies using a powerful magic hidden within its body.

enemy_data.name: Scrambled Energy
enemy_data.library_note: A golden crystalline body of magical power. It is considered to be a legendary existence and rarely ever seen.

enemy_data.name: Disaster Core
enemy_data.library_note: A gigantic crystalline body that is said to have lived since the age of myth. It stands in adventurers' way with great magical power.

enemy_data.name: Earth Plant
enemy_data.library_note: A plant monster that can stand on its feet and move. Its appearance changes drastically depending on the environment.

enemy_data.name: Root Spreader
enemy_data.library_note: A plant monster that adapts to its environment and turns light blue. No one knows why it turns light blue.

enemy_data.name: Great Tree Messenger
enemy_data.library_note: A plant monster that is colored flame red. However it is not actually burning.

enemy_data.name: Great Mistread
enemy_data.library_note: A poisonous-colored plant monster. It is dangerous and said to not be approached if seen.

enemy_data.name: Yggdrasil
enemy_data.library_note: A plant monster that has overgrown due to excessive nutrition. They rampage with excess physical strength, bulldozing the area around it.

enemy_data.name: Rageness
enemy_data.library_note: An ape-like Philuscha which are from the Underworld. Faces fierce competition in the Underworld.

enemy_data.name: Ground Builder
enemy_data.library_note: An ape-like Philuscha that cuts through enemies with its sharp claws. More intelligent and cunning than the regular species.

enemy_data.name: Ruler of the Forest
enemy_data.library_note: An ape-like Philuscha that thrives in the Underworld. Its hardened body hair is a sign of survival.

enemy_data.name: Spark Riser
enemy_data.library_note: An ape-like Philuscha that has risen to the top of its group. Its claws can even slice a rock clean in half.

enemy_data.name: Hell Keeper
enemy_data.library_note: The reason sightings are so few is that its considered to be imaginary and gives everyone nightmares.

enemy_data.name: Giant Sloth
enemy_data.library_note: A few ape-like Philuscha that were able to monopolize food. It's even hated by its own kind.

enemy_data.name: Feral Crow
enemy_data.library_note: A bipedal lizard monster. Hunts down enemies in packs using coordination.

enemy_data.name: Smart Ripper
enemy_data.library_note: A raptor species that has been trained in harsh environments. Hunts more agile and cunningly.

enemy_data.name: Ferocious Hopper
enemy_data.library_note: A raptor species that lives in remote wilderness. Able to leap very high on its developed hind legs.

enemy_data.name: Fierce Hunter
enemy_data.library_note: A species of raptor. If you beat one, they will recognize you as their own. However, due to so many guarding each other, it is not easy.

enemy_data.name: Tyrant
enemy_data.library_note: A Raptor King that leads its group. A strong enemy that fights at the front to protect its friends.

enemy_data.name: Living Armor
enemy_data.library_note: Not sure whether it's a monster clad with armor, or the armor itself is the monster.

enemy_data.name: Ghost Armor
enemy_data.library_note: They often appear at ruins and whisper to adventurers to leave armor behind.

enemy_data.name: Honor Guard Armor
enemy_data.library_note: The official armor of a prosperous country in ancient times. Able to manipulate swordsmanship at will, reflected by the user.

enemy_data.name: Gladiator
enemy_data.library_note: The armor of a warrior who lost his life in a duel. It should be dispersed gracefully, but was captured by magic and resurrected.

enemy_data.name: Legendary Warrior
enemy_data.library_note: Monster armor left behind by a well-known warrior. Even now it is a monster, the swordsmanship remains unchanged.

enemy_data.name: Immortal Knight
enemy_data.library_note: Knight monster who was felled on the battlefield. Its noble soul lives on within its armor, even after death.

enemy_data.name: Royal Admiral
enemy_data.library_note: Said to have been used to direct troops in the old kingdom. Even if there is no king to protect, it will always fight.

enemy_data.name: Heavy Warrior Armor
enemy_data.library_note: Monster armor originally produced for festivals. It was imbued with magic and turned into a monster.

enemy_data.name: Noble Paladin
enemy_data.library_note: A form of armor used by nobility and turned into a monster. It has a desire to rise to the top of the world.

enemy_data.name: Great Guardian
enemy_data.library_note: A guardian monster with a legendary treasure sword and armor. Demonstrates masterful swordsmanship, which shows its performance.

enemy_data.name: Demonic Phantom
enemy_data.library_note: A knight who died without fulfilling his great mission and turned into a monster. The more unfulfilled desires, the stronger it gets.

enemy_data.name: Berserker Shadow
enemy_data.library_note: A monster in armor left behind by a mad warrior called The God of War. Even in death, it continues to yearn for battle.

enemy_data.name: Temple Warrior
enemy_data.library_note: A monster in glass armor. No one knows what is inside the armor.

enemy_data.name: Shattered Breaker
enemy_data.library_note: A monster wearing armor made from amethyst. A meticulous choice of material, but the interior is a mystery.

enemy_data.name: Stinger
enemy_data.library_note: A scorpion-type monster holding sturdy scissors. Once it clips its prey, it won't let go.

enemy_data.name: Sharpened Scissors
enemy_data.library_note: A variant of the Stinger, raised in harsh environments. It is more aggressive and belligerent.

enemy_data.name: Pile Bunker
enemy_data.library_note: A Stinger variant. It has an even harder shell to repel attacks than the normal species.

enemy_data.name: Parching Demon
enemy_data.library_note: It is the highest rank amongst scorpion-type monsters. Their physical strength and intelligence are unmatched compared to the normal species.

enemy_data.name: Sleipnir
enemy_data.library_note: These are exceptionally intelligent scorpion-shaped monsters that can lead other monsters.

enemy_data.name: Dark Scout
enemy_data.library_note: A rat-type monster. It has effective night vision and can target its prey even in the dark.

enemy_data.name: Spine Rat
enemy_data.library_note: A strange looking monster with a hard dorsal fin. It dexterously uses its fin to hunt.

enemy_data.name: Ogre Head
enemy_data.library_note: A rat type monster with sharp horns. Not only its horns, but its scales grow like spines when threatened.

enemy_data.name: Shadow Vanguard
enemy_data.library_note: A relatively mild-mannered rat-type monster. Strongly territorial and hunts in packs.

enemy_data.name: Thrust Hedge
enemy_data.library_note: Utilizing its dorsal fins, this monster excels at underground activities. It will attack you from your blind spot to finish you off.

enemy_data.name: Shadow Eater
enemy_data.library_note: A rat-type monster that excels at stealth. Sneaks up on prey undetected.

enemy_data.name: Legion Needle
enemy_data.library_note: A rat-type monster with sharp needles. The needles can also fire off, useful for both offense and defense.

enemy_data.name: Mini Wyvern
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm. Highly agile due to its small size and can move around in the air to taunt enemies.

enemy_data.name: Zephyr Feather
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm. They are said to have the ability to read the wind and swoop in on the enemy.

enemy_data.name: Evil Orchis
enemy_data.library_note: A wyrm with sharp claws. A blow from its wings can even tear apart metal.

enemy_data.name: Stout Drake
enemy_data.library_note: A pterosaur monster, fat from its overeating. A masterful hunter of prey.

enemy_data.name: Mach Hawk
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm. Their flight speed is said to exceed the speed of sound, but no one has ever seen them fly that fast.

enemy_data.name: Watcher
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm. It is said to have very good eyesight and can detect enemies from far away and prepare for attacks.

enemy_data.name: Draconic Lord
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm with leadership abilities more astonishing than even its own strength. Communicates with other species in an unknown way.

enemy_data.name: Giant Maw
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm. Unlike Stout Drakes, its large figure is all muscles.

enemy_data.name: Mega Wyvern
enemy_data.library_note: A mutated mini wyvern that has grown to a gigantic size. Sometimes accompanied by protospecies as henchmen.

enemy_data.name: King of Storms
enemy_data.library_note: A type of wyrm that suddenly grew huge. Vindictive and doesn't let its prey escape.

enemy_data.name: Cloud Liner
enemy_data.library_note: A pterosaur with an unusually developed sense of smell. Can even detect prey that is out of sight.

enemy_data.name: Landbound Dragon
enemy_data.library_note: It is said that a spirit was bound to the land and took the form of a powerful wyrm to dissipate its unfulfilled desires.

enemy_data.name: Cursed Wing
enemy_data.library_note: Shadow dragon rarely appear in places where war took place. It is said that if you see them, misfortune will befall you.

enemy_data.name: Armored Wing
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm with a steel-colored shell. No ordinary weapon can wound it.

enemy_data.name: Steel Raptor
enemy_data.library_note: A species of wyrm that has developed a greenish-blue color over the years. Its rusted yet unfading shell repels attacks.

enemy_data.name: Sprinting Bird
enemy_data.library_note: A species called a runner with strong legs. Good at running, but not so good at flying.

enemy_data.name: Massive Beak
enemy_data.library_note: A species of roadrunner with a huge beak. A blow from its beak, which gains momentum by running at a fast pace, is frightening.

enemy_data.name: Albatross
enemy_data.library_note: A species of running bird with feathers sold at a high price. However, they are too fast to be caught easily.

enemy_data.name: Wild Crest
enemy_data.library_note: A dark running bird species. The feathers have a beautiful cluster when processed and are therefore valued as ornaments.

enemy_data.name: Overwhelming Bird
enemy_data.library_note: A running bird that loves to run all hours of the day and night. They are also noisy and annoying.

enemy_data.name: Twilight Songbird
enemy_data.library_note: A running bird that runs around in the darkness of night. Has a unique ecology that feeds on human memories.

enemy_data.name: Lifeless Shadow
enemy_data.library_note: A reincarnated form of the Twilight Songbird after death. Its power increases with number of memories consumed during its life.

enemy_data.name: Twilight Assassin
enemy_data.library_note: A Philuscha with distinctive giddy eyes. Extends its long tongue to eat and attack.

enemy_data.name: Cloak-in-dagger
enemy_data.library_note: A Philuscha with a thorny shell. Can be deadly if it hits a body blow.

enemy_data.name: Shadow Assassin
enemy_data.library_note: A Philuscha with a voracious appetite. Swallows trees and even pieces of rock without concern.

enemy_data.name: Cipher Code
enemy_data.library_note: A strong Philuscha that has won the fight for food. Even the Oren struggle with its quick tongue attacks.

enemy_data.name: Hell Keeper
enemy_data.library_note: The giggling Philuscha, who has grown to a large size. Slow in movement, but quick with its tongue.

enemy_data.name: Slashblader
enemy_data.library_note: An agile wolf-like monster. Highly intelligent and utilizes armaments left behind by humans.

enemy_data.name: Spellblade Wielder
enemy_data.library_note: A wolf-like monster that is more fluffy than the normal species. Their pelts fetch a high price on the market.

enemy_data.name: Crimson Arms
enemy_data.library_note: A wolf-like monster with a reddish discoloration. The discoloration is caused by the magic power in the armor it wears.

enemy_data.name: Demon Slayer Wolf
enemy_data.library_note: A monster wearing a powerful magical tool created in ancient times. Shining as silver as the moon.

enemy_data.name: Sleipnir
enemy_data.library_note: A wolf-like monster that has fought many battles in the past. The attacks from its developed body are strong.

enemy_data.name: Hide Shark
enemy_data.library_note: This one has a shark-like appearance but can move on land. People are still investigating as to why it looks like this.

enemy_data.name: Megamouth
enemy_data.library_note: A shark-like monster. It has a well developed jaw that can even chip rocks.

enemy_data.name: Spinal Fin
enemy_data.library_note: A shark-like monster. Its hardened dorsal fin contains a unique composition and is treated as a new-type of mineral.

enemy_data.name: Grand Tusk
enemy_data.library_note: A shark-like monster. They dig holes to make their nests and their territory is full of pits.

enemy_data.name: Sandstorm Tyrant
enemy_data.library_note: A ferocious shark-like monster known as a tyrant. It seizes its prey and drags it straight to the ground.

enemy_data.name: Desert Lagoon
enemy_data.library_note: A shark-like monster often found in sandy areas. Can swim through the desert like an ocean.

enemy_data.name: Mind Ravager
enemy_data.library_note: A shark-like monster that devours memories. Particularly likes emotions such as anger and irritation.

enemy_data.name: Land Crawler
enemy_data.library_note: A blue fish-like monster that has evolved by an insatiable desire to reach land. Advances on its well-developed paws.

enemy_data.name: Soul Cleaver
enemy_data.library_note: A former sea creature that has adapted to land and has fought many generations of battles. With their well-trained fins, they can even fight land-based enemies.

enemy_data.name: Dark General
enemy_data.library_note: A powerful species of Philuscha that bears the name of a general. Its power comes from the Fairystone on its back.

enemy_data.name: Cluster Beetle
enemy_data.library_note: A species of Philuscha. It wields two well-developed horns and runs wild.

enemy_data.name: Shadow Commander
enemy_data.library_note: A stronger species of Philuscha that leads monsters in the Underworld. Rarely appears on the frontlines, but is very vicious.

enemy_data.name: Horned Demon
enemy_data.library_note: The strongest of the Philuscha. Not even a band of warriors from the Oren Tribe could take it down.

enemy_data.name: Rhino Fiend
enemy_data.library_note: Although small for its size, it has a strong body and is not often attacked due to its rampant behavior.

enemy_data.name: Old Castle Dragon
enemy_data.library_note: A gigantic flying dragon that makes its home in old ruins and abandoned buildings. They have a variety of attacks such as fireballs and tornadoes.

enemy_data.name: Dragon Lord
enemy_data.library_note: Originally a gentle dragon that watched over people but lost itself due to evil power.

enemy_data.name: Dragon of Light
enemy_data.library_note: A mysterious dragon whose dwelling and ecology are shrouded in mystery. Worshipped as a god in some regions.

enemy_data.name: Ravaging Queen
enemy_data.library_note: Reigning Queen of the Philuscha. Undermines and destroys everything.

enemy_data.name: Queen of Shadows
enemy_data.library_note: A jet-black queen whose entire body is cursed. Originally just a mere puppet.

enemy_data.name: Crownless Queen
enemy_data.library_note: A gigantic monster, much like the queen of the Philuscha. People fear her as much as calamity itself.

enemy_data.name: Floating Skeleton
enemy_data.library_note: A gigantic skeleton that floats in the air and moves autonomously. Both arms of steel require the utmost caution.

enemy_data.name: Skeleton Emperor
enemy_data.library_note: An enhanced species of Floating Skeleton. A special alloy provides additional hardness as well as flexibility.

enemy_data.name: Automaton
enemy_data.library_note: A giant soldier that appear to have been artificially created. The magic power that pervades its entire body emits light.

enemy_data.name: Sentry Guard
enemy_data.library_note: A high-level version of the Automaton. It shines with the color of brass. Mobility increased by detaching some of its armor.

enemy_data.name: Elder Treant
enemy_data.library_note: A giant plant-like life form lying deep in the forest. It has the power to change the entire environment around it.

enemy_data.name: Ancient Dragon
enemy_data.library_note: A giant life form that has been transformed by stealing the life force of its surroundings. Its open petals deceive humans and siphon off their power.

enemy_data.name: Deranged King
enemy_data.library_note: A giant King of the Philuscha species and lives deep in caves. Even its already robust shell becomes even more robust.

enemy_data.name: Gatekeeper
enemy_data.library_note: An artificial weapon for protecting ruins, powered by the Seeds of Light. What is its biological appearance a reference to?

enemy_data.name: Code of the Universe
enemy_data.library_note: A self-supporting defense weapon that lies in the deepest part of the Code of the Universe. Its mechanism cannot be unraveled by modern technology.

enemy_data.name: Orig. Code of the Universe
enemy_data.library_note: A forgotten weapon found at the top of the central tower on Rosca Island.
